details: Open daily 10:00 - 18:00.

name: The Black Dog Deli
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00, closed Sun.

name: The Bike Side
address: Unit 15, The Huffwood Trading Est. Partridge Green, West Sussex, RH13 8AU
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 9:00 - 14:00. Serves coffee, cold drinks, ice-cream as well as repairs. On an industrial estate, so not pretty, but could be handy.

name: The Sidings Garden Kiosk
address: The Old Railway (pub), Upper Station Rd, Henfield, BN5 9PJ
details: Open daily from 12:00. Literally on the Downs Link cycle path.

name: Pavillion Cafe
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:30 - 15:00, closed Sun & Mon. Literally a minute from NCN 1 in occasionally sunny Montrose, this cafe has Sheffield stands and outdoor seating. Oh, and gorgeous cake.

name: Hall Farm Barn Walk In Cafe
address: Hill Farm, Northchurch Common, Berkhamsted HP4 1LS
details: Closed Winter. Open Fri - Mon 10:00 - 16:00, closed Tues - Thurs. Good coffee, cake and savouries.  Also goats and guinea pigs for the kids to feed.

name: The Tearoom
address: Oak Tree Farm, Wetheral, Carlisle CA4 8JA
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. Garden seating with donkeys in adjacent paddock, nice little gift shop too. Can recommend the baked potatoes and toasties.

name: 32 Broad Street
details: Open daily 8:00 - 15:00, Sun 9:00 - 15:00. A  very cycle friendly stop - bike storage off street, heaters, big garden with covered seating available, indoor seating too and great value coffee, cake and more. Well worth a look. It’s through the arch on the right as you head down Broad Street.

name: The Tea Shed
address: Dog Lane Fishery, Dog Lane, Napton on the Hill, Southam CV47 8LT
details: Open Wed - Sun 8:30 - 14:00, closed Mon & Tues. Open for the fishing season March to end of October.

name: Embers
address: Green Wood Centre, Station Rd, Coalbrookdale, Telford TF8 7DR
details: Open Tues-Sat 9:00 – 15:00. Sun 9:00-16:00. Fantastic coffee shop situated in an idilic woodland ..

name: The Missing Sock
address: Finders Corner, Newmarket Rd, Cambridge CB25 9AQ
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Great place, plenty of outside space and the Mars Bar Brownie is amazing.

name: Mangerton Mill
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00, closed Mon.  Lovely cafe in a working water mill. Hearty food. Welcomes cyclists. Can sit by the river. Can be busy on Sunday Lunches.

name: The Old School House
details: Open Tues - Sat 8:30 - 18:00, Sun 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon. Really friendly staff, lovely food, plenty of bike parking at the rear of the shop and outside seating. Well worth a visit. If going in a group of more than 6 I’d advise ringing ahead and book the tables in advance.

name: Mursley Farm Shop
address: Oliver's Field, Whaddon Rd, Mursley, Milton Keynes MK17 0PL

name: Bigods Kitchen
details: Open Tues - Sun 9:00 - 16:00, Closed Mon.

name: Sea SaltSeaSalt Bistro & Takeaw
address: 57 Frederick Cres, Port Ellen, Isle of Islay PA42 7AY
details: Open daily 10:00 - 14:30 & 17:00 - 21:00, closed Su

name: Ardnahoe Distillery Visitor Centre Cafe
address: Ardnahoe, Port Askaig, Isle of Islay PA46 7RU
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00. Stunning views across the Sound of Jura to the Paps of Jura.

name: Old Kiln Cafe at Ardbeg Distillery
details: Open daily 10:00 0 17:00, closed Sat & Sun. Theres a funky camper van conversion for coffees too!

name: Fenwick Coffee Shop
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00.

name: Moor View Cabin
address: Dobrudden Caravan Park, Baildon, Shipley BD17 5EE
details: Open Wed - Fri 10:00 - 14:00, weekends 10:00 - 15:00, closed Mon & Tues. Another quirky one, up a track that is gravel but you can use road bike, its just not perfect surface! On top of Baildon Moor in  West Yorkshire. Lovely views and a restful place to have a break.

name: Teashop By The Canal
address: The Stone Building The Wharf, Newbury RG14 5AS
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:30.

name: Cotswolds Distillery Visitor Centre, Shop and Cafe
address: Phillip's Field, Whichford Road, Stourton, Shipston-on-Stour CV36 5EX

name: Hook Norton Brewery
address: Brewery Ln, Hook Norton, Banbury OX15 5NY

name: Ionad Chaluim Chille Ile
details: Open weekdays 10:30 - 15:30, closed weekends. Located within Islay's Gaelic Centre. Superb views over loch to Bruichladdich Distillery and big sands.

name: Port Askaig Hotel and Stores
address: Port Askaig, Isle of Islay PA46 7RD
details: Always open. Hotel has light bites , teas , coffees , meals etc.

name: The Secret Tea Garden at Assynt Aromas
details: Open Summer Sun - Thurs 10:00 - 16:30, Cosed Fri & Sat. Cakes and coffee, as well as soaps etc, hence their Facebook page.

name: The Elphin Tearooms
details: Open daily 10:30 - 16:00. Fantastic views of Col Mor.

name: Village Green Coffee Shop
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:30 - 16:30, Sat 9:00 -16:00, Sun 10:00 -14:00 closed  Mon.

name: Bearstone Fruit Farm
details: Open during the fruit picking and pumkin season  There are picnic benches and a hut, with hot and cold drinks, snacks and cakes. Portaloos

name: Hungers Heath Tea Room
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:00

name: The Old Pier
details: Open daily 9:00 -17:00

name: Mint & Ginger Coffee House
address: Main Street, Tur Langton, Leicester LE8 0PJ
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:00 -17:00, Sun & Mon 9:00 -16:00

name: The Ropewalk
address: Maltkiln Road, Barton upon Humber, Lincolnshire, DN18 5JT
details: Closed Mon, Tues, Open Wed - Sat 10:00 -17:00, Sun & BH Mon 10:00 - 16:00

name: The Cartshed Tearoom
address: Church Lane, Station Rd, Great Massingham, King's Lynn PE32 2HY
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00

name: Mulberry Cafe
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:00 – 15:30, Sun 9:30 – 14:30, closed Mon. Plenty of outdoor seating on the green.

name: Sturgate Airfield Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00 - 14:45. Good value cafe, bacon baps, breakfasts, cake etc, tea and coffee (instant). Cards and cash. Plenty of outdoor seating with a view of the planes coming and going on a good day.

name: Whitechurch
details: Open daily 10:00 - 22:00. offee, scones, cakes, sandwiches (and also more substantial meal, booking required). No bike racks, but plenty of space for bike parking in their yard at the back. It can get quite busy, esp. on weeked afternoons.

name: The Old Flight House
address: Medley House, Northampton Rd, Weston-on-the-Green, Bicester OX25 3TJ

name: Yankee Heaven
address: Canal Wharf, Canal St, Littleborough OL15 0HA
details: Open Mon - Thurs 10:00 - 17:00, Fri & Sat 10:00 - 20:00, Sun 11:00 - 16:00. Standard coffee choices, small selection of cake, but the main draw is the ice cream. If you have space in your jersey you can grab a candle while you're there. Space to sit outside on their benches or on the green area beside the canal.

name: Torworth Grange Farm Shop
address: Great North Rd, Torworth, Retford DN22 8NY
details: Open Wed - Sun 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. Lots of outdoor seating and lovely food

name: The INNings at Bangor Cricket Club
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, Sun 11:00 - 17:00. Just off Lôn Las Ogwen & Route 5. Able to keep our bikes at the front in view.  A good menu choice, great coffee and we were made very welcome.  Beautiful views of the mountains. They said we could always arrange to park at the start of a ride if we were then eating there afterwards.

name: The Carriage
address: 12 Old Station Cl, Crawley Down, Crawley RH10 4TX
details: Open daily 9:30 - 10:30, closed Mon. Convenient cafe stop on London Brighton route. Great outdoor area infront , friendly and attentive service. Interesting menu as well.

name: The Riverbank
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, closed Sun. Serves great cake and coffee.

name: The Courtyard Cafe at Petersfield Museum
details: Open Wed - Sat 10:00 - 17:00, Sun 11:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. The Cafe is open to everyone, not just museum visitors. Access to the Courtyard Cafe is separate to the Museum. Simply walk through the gate on the left side of the Museum, into the Courtyard and the Cafe is in the left corner.

name: The Chilli Bean Cafe at Oak Mere Alpacas
address: Newpool Farm, Cheese Hill Ln, Oakmere WA6 8LF
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:30, closed Mon. Nice little cafe and a good alternative to Delamere Station.

name: Comestibles
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:30, closed Sun.

name: Bird & Carter
address: Chilhampton Farm, Warminster Rd, A36, Salisbury SP2 0AB
details: Open Mon - Sat 9:00 - 16:00, closed Sun.

name: Baskervilles Ice Cream Parlour and Coffee Shop
address: 2 Ford St, Moretonhampstead, Newton Abbot TQ13 8LN
details: Open Mon - Wed 10:00 - 16:00, Thurs - Sun 9:30 - 17:00. Excellent place - good outside seating with lots of bike racks and great selection of food. Had the ploughman’s which was huge. Highly recommended.

name: Sgwd Gwladys
address: Pontneddfechan Road, Pontneddfechan, Glynneath, Neath, SA11 5NR
details: Open Sun - Thurs 9:00 - 21:00, Fri & Sat 9:00 - 22:00.

name: Mhor 84
details: Open daily 8:00 - 21:00. Excellent Soup & Sarnies. Recommended. Possibly some of the friendliest staff encountered.

name: Earnespie Farm
address: Earnespie Farm Centre, Old Military Rd, Castle Douglas DG7 3JG
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00.

name: CatStrand
address: High St, New Galloway, Castle Douglas DG7 3RN
details: Open Thurs - Sun 11:00 - 15:00. Off the A762 just as you enter the town from the North. The venue is an arts centre with a cafe.  There is plenty of space outside to leave bikes, but no dedicated bike parking.  Tables are available inside and out.

name: The Ark
details: Open daily 11:00 - 16:00. Right at the end of the road. Offers a lunch menu and is currently outside seating only.  There are a number of tables and picnic benches outside the cafe, but also plenty of other benches in the vicinity.Kippford is signed off the A710 south of Dalbeattie.  It is a no through road, but is possible to ride up the hill at the side of the cafe and access a path, which takes you to Rockcliffe.  Path probably not suitable for full on road bikes.

name: Loch Arthur Farm Shop and Cafe
address: LOCH ARTHUR CAMPHILL COMMUNITY, Beeswing, Dumfries,DG2 8JQ
details: Open Mon - Sat 9:30 - 16:30, closed Sun. Just outside Beeswing (great name!) halfway between Castle Douglas and Dalbeattie, just off the A711. Seating available inside and out. Bike stands available in the car park, but it would also be possible to wheel bikes through the gate, which is the access point to the cafe - especially if sitting outside.

name: Iain Burnett's Highland Chocolatier
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00

name: Streetlights Coffee House
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. Food is amazing and you should dare to see the selection of cakes.

name: The Pavilion Cafe & Bar
details: Open Saturday when there's a match on, and possibly on Sunday mornings.Fab homemade cake. It's at the football club so can be busy

name: Hilltop Farm Cafe
address: St Bartholomews Way, Melton Mowbray, LE14 3JU
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30, hot food until 15:30.Lots of cycle racks and outside seating.

name: The Sea Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00. Excellent coffee and a cycle rack and lots of outside seating. Plenty of other space for bikes. Right by the coastal cycle path.

name: Wood & Green Cafe
details: Open Wed - Sat 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 - 17:00, closed Mon & Tues. Great for coffee and cake for all riders at the Wadebridge end of the Camel Trail. Bike hire (and help) next door from the lovely people at Bridge Bike Hire!

name: Lerryn River Stores
details: Open daily 8:00 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 - 16:00. Not a proper cafe but a great option in good weather. They serve hot food and drinks as well as great cakes and bring it out to you on one of the picnic tables on the adjacent green. The setting is stunning.

name: Apple Cafe
address: West Acre Gardens, Tumbleyhill Rd, King's Lynn PE32 1GE
details: Open daily 10:30 - 15:30, closed Mon. In a lovely rural location in a garden, is very friendly and does great cakes and food. Well worth a detour. Seasonal, open mid April to end September each year.

name: Flight Deck Cafe at Tatenhill Airfield Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00  This is a great little cafe. Limited indoor seating but lots of outdoor benches. Watch the planes with a bacon sandwich.

name: Copper Kettle Tea Rooms
details: Open daily 10:00 - 18:00. Great cafe with a court yard at the rear with access either through the cafe or from a lane at the rear.

name: The Tea Deck
address: Dukes Head Inn, Front Street, Armathwaite, Cumbria, CA4 9PB
details: Very cyclist friendly, a perfect stopping spot in a great cycling area. We loved the sandwiches thé cakes looked perfect too!

name: Mustard Seed Cafe at St Kanes Church Centre
address: 1 Fordyce Terrace, New Deer, Turriff AB53 6WE
details: Open Mon - Fri 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sat, Sun

name: Llangurig Post Office
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 16:00, Sat 9:00 - 13:00, closed Sun. Does hot drinks, pastries and pasties etc, with picnic benches on green across the road. Not a cafe, but a nice, friendly refreshment stop on Lon Las Cymru /Sustrans Route 8.

name: Lowry's At The Chandlery
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. This is a great cafe with a varied menu.

name: Flint Barn Cafe
details: Open Tues - Fri 10:00 - 17:00, Sat - Mon 8:30 - 17:00. Great coffee, cake and vegetarian food.

name: Royal Oak
details: Open Wed 12:00 - 22:30, Fri - Sun 12:00 - 00:00, closed Mon, Tues, Thurs.  Is making cyclists very welcome. See Facebook page for photo's.

name: Porkies Diner
address: Two Shires Park, Weston Road, Evesham WR11 7QF
details: Open Mon - Fri 7:30 -14:30, Sat 7:30 - 13:00, Sun 8:30 - 12:00. Classic Cafe on industrial estate. Large portions and very friendly.

name: Raphael's
address: Hampton Ferry, Boat Lane, Evesham WR11 4BP
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00. closed Mon, Tues no food service.

name: Derya's Cafe
details: Open Wed - Mon 8:00 - 18:00, closed Tues. Very friendly with indoor and outdoor seating.

name: The Old Potting Shed
address: Brook House Farm Campsite, Crew Green, Shrewsbury SY5 9AT
details: Open daily 9:00 - 21:00.

name: The Village Tea room
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16 -000, Sat 9:00 - 15:00, closed Sun.

name: The Clubhouse
details: Open Sun - Thurs 8:30 - 21:00, Fri & Sat 8:30 - 23:00.

name: Toni's Tea Room
details: Open Tues - Thurs 9:00 - 17:00, closed Mon.

name: Ali's of Weybourne
details: Open Mon-Sat 8:30 - 15:00. Sun 9:00 - 15:00 Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Teles Patisserie
address: The Covey, Norwich NR14, The Covey, Norwich NR14 7GD
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon.

name: Applegreen fillingstation
address: Tall Trees Filling Station, Tarporley Rd, Lower Whitley, Warrington, WA4 4EZ
details: Costa Open daily 7:00 - 16:00. Greggs  weekdays 6:00 - 16:00, Sat 7:00 - 16:00, Sun 8:00 - 16:00. Plenty of outdoor seating (as well as being able to eat inside) and the (scrupulously clean) toilets were open.

name: Blu Savannah
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00, weekends 9:00 - 17:00. A snack cabin in a fantastic location overlooking Bridlington North Bay, right on NCN1, behind the Ship Inn. Serving coffees, snacks & ice cream. No indoor seating but plenty of benches but who wants to sit inside with views like this?

name: The Sawmill Cafe & Farm Shop
details: Open Sun - Thurs 9:00 - 17:00, Fri & Sat 9:00 - 19:00.

name: Woodland's Tea Room
address: Santon Bridge, Nr Holmrook, Cumbria CA19 1UY
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. Plenty of outdoor seating.

name: Berry’s Coffee House
details: Open Daily  9.00 - 17.00 Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Edelweiss cafe
details: Open Daily  8:30 - 18:00, Closed from mid December until early Feb

name: Cobbs at Englefield
address: Wickcroft Farm Cottages, Pangbourne Rd. Theale, Reading. RG7 5EA

name: Honesty Inkpen
address: Great Common, Inkpen Common, Hungerford RG17 9QR
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30

name: The Arden Centre
address: Little Alne, Wootton Wawen, Warwickshire B95 6HW
details: Open daily 10:00 -16:00

name: Coco’s Coffee
address: The Old Fire Station, High Street, Blagdon N Somerset, BS40 7RA
details: Open Tues - Sat 10:00 -16:30, closed Sun, Mon

name: Espresso Barn
address: Long Marston Grounds, Station Rd, Long Marston, Stratford-upon-Avon CV37 8RP
details: Open Mon -Fri 10:00 - 15:00, Sat & Sun 9:00 -16:00

name: Meadgate Cafe
address: Meadgate Farm Shop, Weekesley Ln, Timsbury, Bath BA2 0NH
details: Open daily 9:30 - 15:30, closed Sun & Mon. Plenty of outdoor seating, and space to park the bike.  Good selection of food and tea in a proper sized pot.

name: Pumpkin
address: Unit 1, The Borough Mall the Borough, Wedmore BS28 4EB
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00, closed Sun. Friendly staff, good food, indoor and outdoor seating.

name: Open Sky Cycles
address: Heacham Bottom Farm, Lynn Road, Snettisham, PE31 7PQ
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00, Sun 9:00 - 13:00, closed Wed.

name: The Weir cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00. Fabulous breakfast & scummy cakes (especially the scones, freshly made on the premises)

name: Kilbride cafe
address: 9 West Kilbride, Isle of South Uist HS8 5TT
details: Open Mon - Thurs 8:30 - 15:00, Fri & Sat 8:30 - 17:00, Sun 11:00 - 15:00. Breakfasts, toasties, cakes; inside and outside seating.

name: The Noost
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon. Fabulous home-made cakes, coffee, sandwiches, ice-creams. Outdoor seating only.

name: H'Artisan
details: Open daily 8:00 - 17:00. Secure indoor bike racks inside the cafe to keep the bikes safe (with a wide access door), and had outdoor tables through the cafe at the back.

name: Pierreponts cafe
details: Open Wed - Sun 9:30 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. Outside tables with a coffee/cake serving hatch, or you can also eat inside. No secure bike racking unfortunately but eating outside means you can keep an eye on them easily. Extensive brunch type menu and decent cakes also. Ideal for cycling the Thames path.

name: Granites Coffee Shop
address: Mount Sorrell Heritage Centre,240 Swithland Lane, Rothley, Leicestershire.LE7 7UE
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:45.

name: Grange Tea Rooms
address: Ulverscroft Grange, Whitwick Rd, Copt Oak, Markfield LE67 9QB
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sun.

name: Buttermarket cafe
details: Open daily 8:00 - 14:00, Sun 9:00 - 13:00. Outdoor seating under the original buttermarket. Very friendly & value for money.

name: University Park House Bar
address: Park House, Whiteknights Campus, Reading RG6 6UA
details: Open for food Mon - Sat 12:00 - 20:00, Sun 12:00 0 18:30. Not much choice of cakes unfortunately but coffee, drinks and snacks (sandwiches, etc) as well as pub style meals, plenty of outdoor tables (at the front of the cafe) and secure bike parking all around. You don't need to be a member of the University to go here,

name: The Bake-Well
details: Open 8:30 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00. Good selection of home made savouries and cakes and specialise in chocolate brownies. Outdoor seating in front of the cafe.

name: Bobby's Cafe
address: The Stratford Greenway, Seven Meadows Rd, Stratford-upon-Avon CV37 9LE
details: Open Mon 9:00 - 15:00, Tues - Thurs 9:00 - 16:00, Fri & Sat 9:00 - 22:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00. There are two old railway carriage cafes on the Stratford Greenway (Sustrans route). This is the one nearest Stratford. It is next to the cycle hire (Next carriage) so obviously lots of cycle friendly stuff about. Great bacon and egg bap and coffee. Opening hours may need updating.

name: Park End Kitchen
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00, Sat 10:00 - 15:30 & 16:30 - 20:00, Sun 9:00 - 15:00. closed Mon. Happy to fill Bidons, and charge electric bikes

name: Coastal Kitchen
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00, closed Thurs.

name: Bleadon Farm Shop & Cafe
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 14:00, Sat 9:00 - 16:00, Sun 9:00 - 13:00. Lovely ham and cheese baguettes (very fresh) and very good coffee. Not much in the way of cakes but a good selection of sweet pastry.

name: Cwtch Cafe at Acorn Caravan & Camping at Rosedew Farm
address: Acorn Camping & Caravan Site, Ham Lane South, Llantwit Major CF61 1RP
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00 for coffee & cakes, kitchen is closed Mon. . Breakfast 9:00 - 12:00, light lunches 12:30 - 15:00. Cyclists welcome.

name: The Stag at Mentmore
address: The Green, Mentmore, Leighton Buzzard LU7 0QF
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00 & 17:00 - 23:00. Sun 10:00 - 22:00, closed Mon. Very cyclist friendly. Vending machine of bike spares, track pump and lovely food at reasonable prices. 3 ways in all up hill.

name: Saffy's
address: 18 Walton Rd, Stockton Heath, Warrington WA4 6NL
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:30 - 14:30, Sat 9:00 - 14:00, closed Sun & Mon. Great little shop with room for your bikes and to sit round the back.

name: The Beach Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00.

name: Willow Tree Farm
details: Closed Mon. Open Tues - Sun 9:000 -17:00

name: Mae’s Tea Rooms
address: Uldale Old School, Uldale, Cumbria CA7 1HA
details: Open daily 10:30 - 16:30. Great scone and coffee.

name: Torwood Garden Centre Falkirk
address: Central Park, Bellsdyke Rd, Larbert FK5 4EG
details: Open 9:00 - 17:30, Sun 10:00 - 17:30. Choice of two cafes. Sounds like one for coffee & cakes and a second for more substantial meals.

name: House of Meg
details: Closed  Wed. Open Thurs - Tues 10:00 - 15:00

name: Cadence Cycle Cafe
address: Warren Valley Farm Truleigh hill, Shoreham-by-Sea BN43 5FB
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00. Shelter in open sided barn, sit on hay bales, and drink excellent coffee. Two portaloos. Plenty of bike parking. At the top of Mill Hill (if you're on a road bike) and on the South Downs Way (if you're off roading).Very close to Truleigh Hill YHA which also has a cafe, but Cadence is aimed specifically at cyclists.

name: Graffham Village Shop
details: Open weekdays 7:00 - 19:00, Sat 7:30 - 19:00, Sun 8:00 - 17:00. Does coffee, pastries & sandwiches. Bike parking. Seats outside.

name: The Spoke
details: Open weekdays 7:30 - 22:00, Sat 8:00 - 22:00, Sun 8:00 - 21:00. On the corner of Holloway Rd and Marlborough Rd Very friendly to cyclists. Great food.  Note that the door stop is a bike pump. Admire the lovely 1920s building from the outside before having breakfast, lunch, snacks or dinner.  Tons of vegan options too.

name: The Bothy at Boglily
details: Open Mon - Thurs 10:00 - 16:00, Fri - Sun 9:00 - 16:00. Great coffee and a bacon roll. Plenty of space for bikes. There is a covered area, as well as indoor cafe and farm shop.

name: Cafe Shrub
address: Land of Oak & Iron Centre, Spa Well Road, A694, Winlaton Mill, Blaydon-on-Tyne NE21 6RU
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16:00, Weekends 9:00 - 17:00. Sausage rolls are highly recommended.

name: Brownie Barn
address: Howgill Barn, Howgill Lane, Barden BD23 6DJ
details: Open daily 9:00 -17:00

name: Coffee House
address: Millfields Hall, Coach Street, Skipton BD23 1LQ
details: Closed Mon - Wed, Open Thurs - Sat 9:00 -16:00, Sun 10:00 -16:00

name: Kilnsey Park
details: Open Daily 9:00 -17:00

name: The Forge
details: Closed Mon, Tue sOpen Wed - Sun 10:00 -16:00. Good outdoor seating, plenty of space for bikes, quick service.

name: The Mount Vineyard
address: The Mount, Church St, Shoreham, Sevenoaks TN14 7SD
details: Open Wed - Thurs 10:00 - 14:00, Fri - Sun 10:00 - 15:00, closed Mon & Tues. Well worth a visit. Seating area next to the vines.

name: Potters Fish
address: Fishermans Huts, Lifeboat Compound, Selsey, PO20 0DL
details: Open Thurs & Fri 10:30 - 14:30, Sat & Sun 10:30 - 15:00, closed Mon - wed. Serves fresh crab and lobster rolls, salads etc caught by the families own boats just off the coast of Selsey. Lovely place to stop if you're riding the Manhood loop !

name: Time.... The Vintage Hub
address: 7, The Square, Market Pl, Uttoxeter ST14 8HN
details: Open weekdays 9:30 - 16:30, Sat 9:30 - 15:30, closed Sun & Mon.

name: Sunrise Cafe
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00, Sun 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon.

name: Fittleworth Stores
details: Open weekdays 8:30 - 17:30, Sat 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 9:00 - 14:00. Cafe in the rear half of the village shop in Fittleworth. The  store and cafe had the most amazing array of cakes and donuts. Also served fresh sandwiches and sausage rolls and light lunches.  A proper bike rack, lovely outside terrace with plenty of space and cover.

name: The Old Vicarage Tea Room
address: The Old Vicarage, Tosside, Skipton BD23 4SQ
details: Open Mon - Wed 10:30 - 17:00, Fri & Sat 10:00 - 19:30, Sun 10:00 - 17:00, closed Thurs. Good service, VERY  useful location, excellent views. Cash and bank transfer only.

name: Lillypool Farm and Cafe
details: Open daily 8:00 - 15:00. A. Good breakfasts

name: Brig O' Turk Tearoom
details: Open Fri - Sun 10:30 - 16:00. Lovely coffee and cakes, bicycle pump, cycle tool station, lovely part of the world

name: Llyn Brenig Visitor Centre
details: Open daily 8:00 - 15:30. Cafe, picnic area, toilets and bike hire facility in Clocaenog Forest.

name: The Hut At Wheel Worx
address: Platts Cottage, The Parade, Parkgate, Neston CH64 6RW
details: Open Mon - Wed 9:00 - 17:00, closed Thurs, Fri 9:00 - 16:00, weekends 8:00 - 16:00. Has bike racks outside with locks free to use to secure your bike. Has a nice range of cakes and fresh coffee, plus with it being a bike shop it has spares & repairs

name: Humble Bee Cafe
address: Lower Kingcombe, Toller Porcorum, Dorchester DT2 0EQ
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 16:00.  At the Kingcombe Nature reserve Visitor Centre. The cycling is a bit hilly but the cafe is worth it.

name: The Cobbles Cafe & Deli Farm Shop

address: Wheatsheaf Centre, Beechwood Equestrian Centre The, Main Rd, Rettendon Common, Chelmsford CM3 8DY

name: T & Cakes
address: 9 Barrs Ln, North Nibley, Dursley GL11 6DT
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 17:00. A great choice of cakes and paninis/sandwiches/sausage rolls for lunch..

name: Petals Tea Room
address: 61 Manor Rd, Dersingham, King's Lynn PE31 6LH
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 16:30. Closed Mon & Tues. A cyclist friendly tea room serving delicious home made sausage rolls & savouries. A big selection of home made cakes too.

name: Matildas Coffee Shop
address: Next to Butchers Arms, Main St, Fringford, Bicester OX27 8EB
details: Open Mon - Sat  8:30 - 16:30. Closed Sun. The range of homemade cakes is excellent and good value. The cafe is next to the Butchers Arms pub and shares cycle parking and toilets.

name: Garden TIPI
address: Preston Bissett Nurseries, Preston Bissett, Buckingham, MK18 4ND
details: Open daily 10:00 -16:00. Coffee, cakes and light lunches

name: Marina Cafe
address: Devizes Marina Village,Horton Avenue, Devizes, SN10 2RH
details: Open Mon- Sat 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 -17:00. All food is home baked, Italian coffee.

name: Denby's
address: Unit 1, 182 Derby Rd, Denby Village, Ripley DE5 8RD
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 16:00, weekends 9:00 - 16:00. Lovely coffee and cake, outside seating hidden round the back as well

name: Chilbolton Shop & Tearoom
address: Village St, Chilbolton, Stockbridge, Hampshire, SO20 6BE
details: Open weekdays 7:30 - 18:00, Sat 8:00 - 17:30, Sun 8:00 - 14:00. Ridiculously pretty village store and tearoom close toTest Valley cycleway. Great cakes too!

name: The Willow Tree
details: Open Fri - Sun 9:30 - 16:00. It used to be an Otter Sanctuary but is now a cafe and woodland walk.

name: Rectory Farm Kitchen
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00. Great place for food, cake, and coffee.  Good quality ingredients, nice strong coffee, bike rack outside, nice quiet road to get to it, and a small garden as well for those who like to sit outside.

name: Fiskerton Village Store and Post Office
details: Open weekdays 6:00 - 19:00, Sat 7:00 - 18:00, Sun 7:00 - 17:00. A general village store selling anything from cleaning products to fresh vegetables but, more importantly, hot & cold drinks and hot sausage rolls etc plus commercial cakes. Excellent service. There are no seats or bike racks yet but a short distance north there are seats on the banks of the Trent.

name: Lakeside Cafe
address: Wergs Hall Rd, Codsall, Wolverhampton WV8 2HH
details: Open Sun - Wed 8:00 - 15:00, Fri & Sat 8:00 - 16:00, closed Thurs.

name: Sunny Side Up Cafe
address: Sunnyside Rural Trust, Central Nursery, Two Waters Rd, Hemel Hempstead HP3 9BY
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00, closed Sun. The coffee, cakes and ethos are very good. They train and employ people with Learning Disabilities to work in their market garden, plant nursery, shop and cafe. There is inside and outside seating and when I visited today, extra seating in a greenhouse. Plenty of space for cyclists and bikes and deserving of support.

name: The Coffee Stop
address: 7 Little London, Deanshanger, Milton Keynes MK19 6HU
details: Open Mon - Fri 8:30 - 16:30, Sat 8:00 - 15:00, Sun 9:00 - 15:30. Excellent coffee, beautiful savoury baps and bagels, friendly and attentive service.

name: The Greenery
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 15:00, weekends 9:00 - 16:00.  alongside the very popular Holcroft Lane/Glazebrook Lane between Culcheth and the A57. No bike racks but a good solid wall adjacent, very welcoming to us when we called for coffee. VERY nice coffee, cakes looked good too.

name: Cogs & Coffee
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:30 - 16:30, Sat 8:30 - 13:00, closed Sun & Mon. An excellent LBS and coffee shop in Selby. Friendly and knowledgeable owner, delicious coffee and small selection of cakes. Nice small stock of useful extras for your bike.

name: Barleycorn Cafe
address: Barleycorn Hub, Sheldrick Way, Bury Saint Edmunds IP28 7JX
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, later in Summer. Excellent coffee stop on the Cambs/Suffolk border at the end of West Row bridleway. Located within the public library, limited indoor seating for large groups when busy but space outside in summer. Plenty of undercover cycle parking hoops.

name: Whitehall Museum
details: Open Thurs - Sat l10:00 - 17:00.ovely heritage house (free) with a delightful cafe and secluded garden.  Can bring bikes into the garden. Delicious food and homemade cakes.

name: Steam Pump Tea Rooms
address: Museum of Power, Hatfield Road, Langford, CM9 6QA
details: Open Wed - Sun  9:30 -15:00

name: Ethos Bros
address: Langford Court, Kelvedon Hatch, Brentwood CM15 0LB
details: Open Wed- Sun 9:00 - 15:00 Vegan cafe and coffee shop offering hot meals, flatbread, cakes, snacks,

name: Stow Maries Aerodrome cafe
address: Hackmans Lane, Flambird's Chase, Chelmsford CM3 6RJ
details: Open Fri - Sun 10:00 -15:30. Need to get free pass from ticket office for mess hall, and dismount.

name: T' On The Green
details: Open Tues 10:00 - 16:00, Wed - Thurs 8:30 - 16:00, Fri 8:30 - 17:00, Sat 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon. The cafe is very cycling friendly, the owner is a cyclist.

name: Brill Coffee Van
address: Brill Windmill Car Park, South Hills, Brill, Aylesbury HP18 9TQ
details: Open Thurs - Sun 8:00 - 12:00. Located in a van at the car park of the windmill.  No indoors seating or heating, but the biscoff blondies look like a good reward after a sprint up Tramhill.

name: Gawsworth Community Cafe
address: 2 Longbutts Lane, Gawsworth, Cheshire, Macclesfield SK11 9QU
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00, Sun 8:00 - 10:30. Great cafe. Hot and cold food. Opposite the primary school.

name: Gisburn Forest Cafe
address: Stephen Park Dale Head, Clitheroe BB7 4TS
details: Open Wed - Mon 10:00 - 16:00 Closed Tues. Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Clarion Mouse
details: Open Sunday 10:30 -16:00. Tea, Cake and chocholate. Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Langdons
details: Open  Daily 7:00 - 15:30, Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Hartwell Nurseries
details: Open Mon - Sat, 9:00 to 17:30, Sun 10:00 to 16:00

name: Cogs
details: Open Tues - Fri  8:00 - 17:00, Sat - Sun 9:00 - 16;00, Closed Mon

name: Forge Coffee
address: The Paddocks, Whittlebury Park, Towcester, NN12 8QH
details: Open Mon-Fri 8:00-16:00, Sun 8:00-15:00 Follow Forge signs

name: The Cowshed Cafe
address: Oak Farm, Bedford Rd, Northill, Biggleswade SG18 9AW
details: Open Wed - Mon 10:00 - 16:00. Great cycling themed cafe with plenty of seating inside and out plus lots of secure racking for bikes. Sarah and Rob are both cyclists and very good hosts.

name: The Garden Cafe
address: Munnings art Museum, `Castle Hill, Dedham, Colchester CO7 6AZ
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 16:30. Closes for Winter Nov - April. Check website for more details. The Cafe is situated in the grounds of Munnings Art Museum, Dedham

name: Nixons Farm shop and Tea Rooms
address: Outwood Farm, Bolshaw Rd, Heald Green, Cheadle SK8 3PS
details: Closed Mon, Tues untill the end of February for maintence. Open Mon - Fri  9:00 - 17:00, Sat, Sun & BH 9:00 - 16:00. Can be accessed via the A555 cycle path.

name: Halo
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, Mon 10:00 - 15:00, closed Sun. Cafe with great service, good food and drinks. Friendly staff who welcome cyclists. Courtyard setting brings extra security for bikes.

name: The Reading Room Kitchen
address: Holden Clough Nurseries, Holden, Bolton-by-Bowland, Lancashire BB7 4PF
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:00.

name: Coffee & Coe
details: Temp hours only  Thurs Fri 10:00-15:00, Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 16:00. Nice converted barn with heating and log burner. Nice food and fresh. Good coffee and cakes. Warm welcome to cyclists Sits on main road through Bielby. times are changed for xmas so worth checking if going before then.

name: The Shire
address: High Belthorpe Farm, Bishop Wilton, YO42 1SB
details: Open Wed - Fri 9:30 - 16:30, Sat 12:00 - 18:00, Sun 13:00 - 18:00, closed Mon & Tues. Located up a single track road from Bishop Wilton. Road tarmac at first then turns into gravel farm track but is okay for all bikes. Nice food and great location. Plenty of space for leaving bikes and very safe location.

name: Slice of the Broads
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:30, Mon 9:00 - 15:30. Closed Mid Dec - Feb

name: Chestnuts Coffee
address: 2, The Chestnuts, Norwich Rd, Norwich NR16 1EG
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 15:00. Bike rack, excellent offerings of food and drink including a few options for vegans.

name: The Courtyard Brasserie
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:30, Sun 10:00 - 16:30. Just off the main square in Olney, Northants, so bike can easily be left and are out of view of the busy market square.

name: Door 34
details: Open Wed -Mon 9:00 - 16:00 Closed Tues. Plenty of room upstairs. Bikes can go round the back. Vege options.

name: Crate Cafe
address: Broadbridge Business Centre,  Delling Lane, Bosham, Chichester PO18 8NF
details: Open Mon, Tues 9:00-16:00 , Wed 9:00-21:00, Thurs - Sat 9:00-23:00, Sun 10:00 -22:00.oOutdoor seating only but with cover and heating.

name: Birds Bakery
details: Open daily 7:30 - 16:00, closed Sun. Quality is top class. They also do hot food and in throry are open all day but usually sell out by about 15:00. Has a small area set aside for hot and cold drinks and, of course CAKE.A short ride from NCN6 (DerbyCanal Path) at Allenton with cycle racks nearby.

name: The Four Shires Farm Shop
details: Open Wed - Sat 9.30 -2.30 last food orders and closes at 3. Serves breakfast until 11.30

name: Tartan Tearoom
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:30 - 15:30

name: The Village Teapot
address: 63 Liverpool Old Road, Walmer Bridge, Preston, PR4 5QA
details: Open Tues - Fri 9:00 -17:00, Sat 9:30-16:00, Sun 10:00 -14:00, Closed Mon

name: Ridgmont Station Vintage Tea Room and Heritage Centre
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. Food served until 15:00. Very welcoming and pleasant heritage location. Good coffee , cakes and breakfast! Sometimes difficult to see if it is open. There are tables outside but if you want to eat in there is spaces to lock up bikes round the back…

name: Mrs Merton's Tea Room
address: Westmoor Nursery, Westmoor Farm, Moor Street, Rainham, Gillingham, Kent. ME8 8QF
details: Open Mon - Thurs 9:00 - 16:00, Fri & Sat 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00. A friendly, family run tea room. I stopped here whilst out on a ride with Wigmore Cycling Club. Lovely place for a tea / coffee & cake stop. Their cakes are lovely. If you’re more savoury like me, then the homemade sausage rolls & cheese scones are a must! The bonus is there’s a nursery too.

name: Bonnies Tea Room at Wildgoose
address: Old Quarry Drive Main Road, Hallow WR2 6LS

name: Cafe On The Common
address: The Common, Rickmansworth Road, Chorleywood, Herts, WD3 5SG
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00 in winter, 8:30 - 17:00 in summer. Serves homemade breakfasts, light lunches, vegan and vegetarian options, cakes and pastries.community cafe in the cricket club on Chorleywood Common. Open every day for breakfast and lunch as well as coffee & cake. It is run by Mission Employable for people with learning difficulties. Plenty of indoor seating, no outside seating yet but you can always sit in the grass close to your bike.

name: Tatton Perk
address: King Street carpark, Malt Street, Knutsford - opposite the Moor Park
details: Open Mon - Sat 8:00-16:00, Sun 9:00 - 16:00, Coffee cakes, Hot drinks, Locally made cakes, Wraps at the weekend. A frame Bike rack , track pump, inner tubes

name: Fork 'Andles Coffee Shop at Littlehurst Garden Centre
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00. Small but friendly Cafe

name: Sista Barista
address: Unit 1, Queens Head House, The St, Acle, Norwich NR13 3DY
details: Open Mon - Fri 7:30 - 16:30, Sat 9:30 - 16:30, closed Sun. Excellent coffee as you would expect but the food is absolutely wonderful, all home cooked, sausage rolls, and cheese scones are my tip, but there are also cakes! Friendly family run business, currently tucked away just off the high street, worth the search for this hidden gem, soon to be moving to larger premises into the old Barclays Bank for even more selection of cakes and baked goods and they tell me the waffles will be coming back to the menu

name: Stop 'n' Stuff
address: Pure Triumph, George St, Woburn, Milton Keynes MK17 9PY
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:00 - 16:00, closed Sun & Mon. Excellent coffee and snack menu here at Cafe attached to Triumph motorcycle dealership. Tables inside and out.

name: Pixie Bakes Cakery and Coffee Shop
details: Open Tues - Fri 9:30 - 16:00, Sat 10:00 - 15:00, closed Sun & Mon. Cycle friendly, water bottles filled, Wi-Fi and space outside to sit with your bike.

name: The Tower Barn at Broadway Tower
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00.

name: Toast Office
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 15:00, Sat 9:00 - 13:00, closed Sun.

name: Bruno's Bakery
details: Open Mon - Wed 06:00 - 17:00, Thurs Fri 7:00 - 17:00, Sat 6:00 - 14:30, closed Sun. Very smart cafe with a delightful selection of bakeries and meals

name: Cafe Blue
address: Sawley Bridge Marina, Tamworth Rd, Long Eaton, Nottingham NG10 3AE
details: Open daily 8:00 - 17:00. Recently been refurbished. Open 7 days a week. Excellent choice of food, friendly staff and keen to attract cyclists. They offer a discount to those arriving by bike.

name: Woodoaks Tea Shack
address: Denham Way, Maple Cross, Rickmansworth,  Hertfordshire WD3 9XQ
details: Outdoor only Open Wed- Fri 11:00- 15:00, Sat, Sun 10:00 -16:00 Check website forSummer hours

name: Tatton Perk Booths Park coffee shop
address: Booths Park, Hall Car Park, Knutsford WA16 8GS
details: Open Mon-Fri 8:00-16:00, closed Sat,Sun. Seating for 11 inside, in the summer it has deckchairs out on the grass. Toilet facilities in the building next door.

name: Roots Coffee Lounge
address: Landmark Centre, Chesterfield Road, Pleasley NG19 7SP
details: Open Mon-Fri 7:00- 16:00, Sat 9:00-14:00, Closed Sun

name: Tea by the Lock
address: Naburn Banqueting Hall Naburn lock track, York YO19 4RU
details: Open Wed-Sun 10:00-16:00, Closed Mon,Tues. 100% Vegan.

name: Whitburn Village Cafe
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:00, closed Wed. Excellent cafe - meals, snacks and cake, established over 50 years ago.

name: The Leys Bakery and Cafe
address: Robinson's Corner, Sturton Rd, South Wheatley, Retford DN22 9DH
details: Open Wed - Sat 8:30 - 16:00, closed Sun - Tues. Artisan bakery providing excellent food and drinks.  Service is great; staff are very friendly and helpful.

name: The Steading Courtyard
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30, Sun 9:00 - 16:00. Plenty room for bikes. A good menu to choose from and lovely coffee.

name: The Little Lock Cafe
details: Open Mon - Thurs 9:30 - 16:30, Fri 9:00 - 17:00. Sat 9:00 - 17:30, Sun 9:00 - 16:00. It is set back a bit from the centre of the village but is easy to find as it is next to the canal towpath. I was the only cyclist there when I called but it seemed to be a mecca for dog walkers. It is not very big but it does have a seating area overlooking the canal.

name: The Family Tree Tea Room & Nursery
address: The Little House, Thorpe Lane, Cawood, Selby YO8 3SG
details: Open Tues - Fri 9:15 - 14:30, Sat & Sun 10:00 - 14:30. Excellent coffee and home-made cakes, plus bacon butties etc.

name: Brew at 32
address: 32 High St, Lydd, Romney Marsh TN29 9AJ
details: Open Tues - Sat 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sun & Mon. On NCN route 2.

name: Cave (formerly Bloc)
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00, closed Mon.

name: Busk
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:30 - 16:00, Sat 9:00 - 16:00, closed sun & Mon.

name: Kiosk Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues.

name: Baltzersens
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00.

name: Arlo
address: 70 Main St, Burley in Wharfedale, Ilkley LS29 7DF

name: Bottle & Bean
details: Open Wed - Thurs 9:00 - 15:00, Sat 9:00 - 19:00, closed Sun, Mon, Tues.

name: The Clubhouse
details: Open weekdays 7:00 - 16:00, closed Sat & Sun.

name: The Willows
address: 1 Willow Lanen, Cranwell Village, Sleaford NG34 8DE
details: Open 9:00-15:00 every day. Very friendly and fabulous home made cakes, plus bacon rolls and lovely breakfasts etc. Railings for bikes

name: House CoffeeCo.
details: Open Tues-Sat 8:30-16:00 Closed Sun,Mon. Great coffee, smoothies, fresh homemade soups, sandwiches, toasties, cakes etc, vegan stuff too. Indoor and outside seating

name: Colmworth Golf Club
details: Open daily 800-1800 (snacks and drinks only after 1430, Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: The Clubhouse Coffee & Cycles
details: Open Tues - Sat 8:30 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 1500, closed Mon. Great Coffee & Bacon sandwich  Bike rack inside the shop too

name: Wellie Deli
address: 48 Ashby Road, Newbold Coleorton, Coalville, Leicestershire LE67 8PB
details: Open Thurs - Mon 9:30-15:00 Closed Tues,Wed. Indoor & outdoor seating (with log burner)

name: Olivia's at the Outwoods
address: Outwoods Country Park, Woodhouse Ln, Woodhouse Eaves, Loughborough LE11 3YG
details: Open 9:00 - 16:00 Mon - Sat, 10:00 - 16:00 Sun. Indoor and outdoor seating, plenty of places to leave bikes and very possibly THE best brownies in the world. Nice menu (soups, sandwiches, toasties), with breakfasts served up to 11:30.

name: The Courtyard Cafe
address: Unit 20, Tardebigge Court, Hewell Lane, Redditch B97 6QJ
details: Open Mon - Thurs & Sat 9:00 - 14:30, Fri 8:30 - 14:30, Sun 9:30 - 14:00. Small and cozy with a few tables inside, might be worth phoning to check or reserve a place, may not be able to cater for large groups. Nice selection of the normal cafe foods, well cooked and serve reasonably quickly. Toilets available, with key code.

name: White Swan
details: Open Tues - Sat 12:00 - 23:00, Sun 12:00 - 22:30, Mon 12:00 - 22:00. Huge sign on the side of the building saying cyclists and walkers welcome. Bike rack out the front, huge beer garden at the back. All 14 of us left the bikes in the back and all felt safe. Cracking roast beef bap and chips for under a fiver. Great welcome and very accomodating, especially as we were a large group, arriving on mass on a busy Sunday lunch without booking. Highly recommended.

name: The Hangar
address: Fairoaks Airport, Chertsey Rd, Chobham, Woking GU24 8HX
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, closed Sun. On the airport itself next to the runway, so from the outside terrace you can watch the planes and helicopters land and taxi around Inside area too. Nice cakes and cofffee, and also do breakfasts and lunch. It's open to the public as well as pilots and airport staff. Couldn't see bike racks, but lots of space for bikes.

name: World Horse Welfare Hall Farm
details: Open weekends 10:00 - 16:00. Selection of hot and cold food and drinks.Every cup of coffee sold helps to raise money for the charity and make a difference to the lives of the horses and ponies in their care.

name: Lowick Village Store
details: Not a cafe but an excellent coffee and range of pastries/cakes available.

name: Farmers Table
address: Box Walk, Tortworth. Wotton-under-edge, Gloucestershire GL12 8HF
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:00-17:00, closed Sun. Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: Kingfisher Cafe
address: Camley Nature Reserve, 12 Camley St, London N1C 4PW.
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. Mostly outside space, a large canopy gives shelter/shade. Overlooks the Regent's canal. Usually quiet as it's a bit out of the way.

name: L A Cafe
details: Open Mon-Sat 8:00 14:00. Sun 9:00-1400 Aslo 18:00 - 21:00 Mon & Fri Inside is small and can be busy so worth booking if in a group. Bike can be left by the windoq.

name: The Pink Cabbage Co.
address: Old Station, Heathfield, East Sussex, TN21 0AA

name: Delish Formby
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 17:00, weekends 10:00 - 16:00.

name: Julie's

details: Open Wed - Sun 9:30 - 16:30, Thurs 9:30 - 19:00, closed Mon & Tues. Opposite side of road to The Potting Shed

name: Michele’s Cafe

details: Open Mon-Sat 8:30-16:00, closed Sun. Indoor and outdoor seating, good for big groups. Bike racks

name: Little Elf's Kitchen
details: Open Tues - Sat 8:00 - 14:00, Sun 9:00 - 13:00, closed Mon. Nice little cafe, good food and great service, they put tables and chairs out side in good weather.

name: Scottish Dolphin Centre
details: Open Thurs - Mon 10:30 - 16:00, closed Tues & Wed.

name: The Dragonfly Cafe and Nature Centre
address: Wiltshire Wildlife Trust, Lower Moor Farm, Oaksey, SN16 9TW
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. Good friendly service, good food and lovely location.

name: Oddfellows Coffee
address: Oddfellows Hall, Shaftoe St, Haydon Bridge, Hexham NE47 6BQ
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00, closed Tues.

name: The Farm Club
address: Mere View Farm, Park Ln, Pickmere, Knutsford WA16 0LG
details: Open daily 9:00-16:00

name: Kickback Coffee
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 15:00, weekends 9:00 - 16:00. Ideal for gravel riders  due to close proximity of canal path.

name: Albion Bakery
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 15:00, Sat 8:00 - 14:00, closed Sun.

name: Mulberry & Thyme
address: Hillier Garden Centre Newbury,Priors Ct Rd ,Hermitage, Thatcham,RG18 9TG

name: Wendy Lou's Tearoom
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:00-15:00, Closed Sun. Cash only

name: The Meeting Place
address: The Swan at Chaddesley. Briar Hill, Chaddesley Corbett, Kidderminster DY10 4SD
details: Open Sundays only 9:00 - 13:00. In the rear garden is a coffee hut that is cyclist friendly. Plenty of places to sit and keep your bikes close by. Nice coffee too (they had cake/pastry but I didn’t partake).

name: Emmy's Pitta
details: Open daily 9:00 - 23:00. Pittas with chips and tasty fillings (including vegetarian), nice coffee and a few cakes. We sat outside with our bikes against the park wall. Racks nearby if you've got a lock. Friendly and filled our bottles happily including ice. Don't forget to visit the memorial to the inventor of the safety bicycle

name: Cafe Zenn
details: Open daily 9:00 - 22:00.  Plenty of veggie options. .  Good coffee too, and everyone friendly - happy to fill our bottles.  Some bike racks across the road but we've sat outside with our bikes against the lamp posts.

name: Brickyard Cafe
address: Bursledon Brickworks Museum, Swanwick Lane, Swanwick, Southampton, SO31 7HB
details: Open from mid-April Wed, Thurs & Sun 10:00-16:00. Plenty of outdoor space for bikes by tables.

name: Hunters Lodge Fishery
address: 1 Church Street, Elsham, Brigg, N Lincolnshire DN20 0RG
details: Open  Thurs,  Fri 9:00-12:00, Sat, Sun 9:00-14:00

name: On the Latch
details: Open Fri -Sun 8:30-16:00, Mon 8:30-15:00, Tue-Thurs  8:30-15:30 indoor and outdoor seating

name: Minting Park Farm
details: Only open Thurs & Sat 9:00 -16:00. Produce is grown and cooked on the farm. No fancy coffees but a cafeteire of coffee is available. Tea and other drinks are available.  Bike bar to hang the bike.

name: Mousehole Deli & Kitchen
details: Open daily 8:00 - 21:00. perfect stop for a takeaway coffee and cake / pastry / pastie or eating in. Also gourmet restaurant  Lovely food and friendly service.

name: The Wonky Pear
details: Open daily 11:00 - 22:00. Serves hot drinks and an excellent array of homemade cakes in addition to cask beers etc so ok for a tea stop rather than lunch. There is limited cycle parking on the pavement or possibly at the little shop next door with permission. There is seating upstairs and down.

name: The Paddocks Coffee Bar
details: Open weekdays 7:00 - 19:00, Sat & Sun 8:00 - 17:00.

name: Dandelion Coffee
details: Open weekdays 7:00 - 16:00, Sat 8:00 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 16:00, closed Tues. In the centre of Buxton: excellent coffee (and tea), small but delicious cake selection (no savoury food), very friendly. Inside and outside seating. Card payment only. No dedicated bike parking, but there’s lots of wall and railing space just outside.

name: The Badger's Kitchen
address: Brandon Marsh Nature Reserve, Brandon Ln, Coventry CV3 3GW
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:00.

name: Brackley Central Cafe
address: Station House, Top Station Road, Brackley NN13 7UG
details: Open 8:00 -16:00 Sat-Tues, Closed Wed-Fri

name: Puddleduck Cafe & Gallery
address: Holt Farm, Holt Road, Southam, CV47 1AJ
details: Open Fri- Sun (and bank hols) 11am-5pm. Closed Mon -Thurs. Indoor  and outdoor seating. Great cake!

name: Josie's Place
address: 8 High Street, Stockton, Southam, England, CV47 8JZ
details: Open weekdays 7:00 - 17:00, Sat 7:00 - 16:00, Sun 7:00 - 14:00, closed Tues. Great coffee, cakes and hot food!

name: The Boat House Cafe
address: Hazelwood Lakes, Moor Lane, Thorpe On The Hill, Lincoln
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. Cyclist friendly. Lovely outside and inside seating with views of a water skiing lake

name: The Lounge
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Is back open under new management, friendly service, great food, offers to fill up water bottles too.

name: The Tee Room
details: Open daily 8:30-16:00 (may vary seasonally) Indoor and outdoor seating. Always accommodating

name: The Barn
address: Rushett Farm, Leatherhead Rd, Chessington KT9 2NH
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 14:00, weekends 8:00 - 15:00. Outdoor cafe on a working farm accessible only by cycling and walking. Top notch specialty coffee, cabinet full of delicious bakes and the best views you'll ever have whilst sipping a flat white. Excellent Gravel routes right from the door.

name: Maple Park Cafe

details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16:00.Located in the grounds of the Crematorium

name: Fox in the Stables Tearooms

details: Open daily 9:00-16:00. Vegetarian / vegan tearoom. Indoor and outdoor seating space for bikes.

name: Chataways Tea Room & Shop
address: 33, The Barns, Hewell Ln, Tardebigge, Bromsgrove B60 1LP
details: Open Tues-Sat 9:00-15:00 Closed Sun,Mon. Cakes and sandwiches available

name: The Hide
address: Pennington Flash, St Helens Road, Leigh WN7 3PA
details: Open daily 9:00-19:00  (Apr- Oct)   9:00-16:00 (Nov-Mar)  Card payment only. Outside and indoor seating . Plenty of room for bikes, locks available. very clean.

name: Beyond Coffee
details: Open Mon-Fri 8:00-16:30, Sat 8:00-16:00, Sun 9:00-15:00. Next to Co-Op

name: Sandwell tea rooms
details: Open daily 10am - 16:00, breakfast served untill 12:00.Entrance through the visitor centre shop, Small cafe and seating area indoors but plenty of room in the three courtyards.

name: The Buttery
address: GG Express, Manor House Farm, Woodford, Kettering, NN14 4ES
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00. Very cycle friendly with a good range of food and cake.

name: The Dream Bean Cafe
address: 10 The Stables, Offley Hoo Farm, Great Offley, Hitchin SG5 3ED
details: Open weekdays 7:00 - 15:00, weekends 8:00 - 16:00. Fantastic sourdough toasties as well as breakfast baps.

name: Beckbury Community Shop
details: Open daily 9:30 - 15:30. Sells coffee and other items.

name: The Hobo.Co @ The Pottery
address: Farnham Pottery, Quennells Hill, Wrecclesham GU10 4SL
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00. A lovely cafe inside the pottery. Great selection of cakes, coffee/drinks and breakfast items. Also a customer accessible tap/sink for access to drinking water

name: Apple Orchard Cafe
address: The High St, West Wycombe, HP14 3AG
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00. A great cafe with a friendly welcome and great coffee and cakes. It has an enclosed and safe courtyard cafe and a newly installed bike rack. Plenty of room inside if weather dictates. Entry is best via the rear entrance off church lane car-park and down into the garden.

name: Caernarfon Airport Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Not in Caernarfon but not far and it’s a lovely ride to get there along the coast and country lanes or you can use the cycle path from Caernarfon to Porthmadog and get off at Dinas

name: Burneys Cafe
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:00 - 15:00, Sat 8:00 - 12:00, closed Sun & Mon. Great little cafe with delicious coffee situated in crosshills, in between Keighley and Skipton.

name: The Falkirk Wheel Cafe
address: The Falkirk Wheel, Ochiltree Terrace, Falkirk FK1 4LS.
details: Open daily 10.30 to 17.30, easy to keep your bike in sight, great views of the Wheel in operation too. On the Forth & Clyde Canal and at the junction with the Union Canal.

name: Caffi De Winton
address: Welsh Highland Railway, Caernarfon Station, St Helen's Rd, Caernarfon LL55 2PN
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00.

name: Tea Room at Tan y Bwlch Station
address: Ffestiniog Railway, B4410, Blaenau Ffestiniog LL41 3AQ
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00.

name: Giddy Up Teacup
address: John Webb's Windmill, Fish Market St, Thaxted, Essex, CM6 2LD
details: Open weekends and bank holidays in the summer from 10am ish. Cakes, sausage rolls, coffee, and tea in a pot with a cosy. Great people, great service, best location in the world

name: The Village Store
address: 23 Chapel St, Bishop's Itchington, Southam CV47 2RB
details: Open daily 5:00 - 17:00, Sun 5:00 - 12:00. Great coffee, pies and pastries. Smallish, but with good outdoor seating, and very friendly.

name: Pavillion Cafe
details: Open 10:00 - 15:00 daily (winter hours). Check website for summer opening hours. Access by following the signs for disabled parking. Sheffield bike stands at the side of the cafe, or lean bikes against the structure. Seating inside and out. Friendly and helpful staff and a social enterprise.

name: Sweet Boutique
details: Open Tues & Sat 10:00 - 16:30,  Wed - Fri 11:00 - 16:30. A great stop for all your refreshments … coffee, milkshakes, homemade cakes, loose sweets

name: Sudbury Courtyard
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:30 - 16:30, Sun 10:00 - 16:30, closed Mon.

name: Ivy Joys Vintage Tea Room
address: 18 Fleckney Rd, Kibworth Beauchamp, Leicester LE8 0HE
details: Open Wed - Sat 9:00 - 16:00, closed Sun - Wed. Lots of outdoor space at the back for bikes and plenty indoors if the weather is bad.

name: Robert Fletcher Wildlife Artist. Studio & Tea Room
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:30. Great stop off if cyling  around or in Grizedale Forest and South Lakeland.

name: Bessie's Cafe
address: Bessie Bar Cottage, Main St, Culross, Dunfermline KY12 8JQ
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00.

name: Birkheads Secret Gardens, Coffee Shop & Nursery
address: Birkheads Ln, Sunniside, Newcastle upon Tyne NE16 5EL
details: Open Thurs - Sun 11:00 - 15:00 (Winter hours, check website for summer). 2 mins down the road from the bowes railway cycle route or a good stop off after testing silver hills open thurs-sun 11-3

name: Seaview Cafe
address: Port Ban Holiday Park, Tarbert, Argyll PA29 6YD
details: Open Mon - Fri 11:00-15:00, Sat 10:00-16:00 Closed Sun Tables inside and out.  Good range of home cooked cakes.

name: Cobbs Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00-16:00 Cakes,  snacks and meals.  Tables inside and out

name: Plucky Pheasant
details: Open Mon-Fri  8:30-16:30, Sat, Sun & BH 8:30 - 17:00 Indoor and outdoor.

name: Peaslake Village Stores
details: Open: daily 800-1830 (1700 Sun).Popular MTB/bike stop, tea/coffee, cakes, great sausage rolls

name: Dalavich Shop and Wild Rowan Cafe.
details: Open Wed 9:00-17:00, Thur-Sat 9:00-19:00, Sun 10:00-18:00. Closed Mon,Tues. Mostly outside tables. A couple indoors

name: Threaplands Garden Centre
details: Open Mon - Sat 9:00.-17:00.,Sun 10:00 -17:00. Great food and coffee. Bike rack, marquee area

name: Hopeman Sands Cafe
details: Open Tues-Sun 10:00-16:00 Closed Mon. All day breakfasts, hot and cold food, coffee and cake.  Park bikes on street but nobody seems to worry about bikes here!

name: The Apiary Dalwhinnie
address: The Lodge, Station Road, Dalwhinnie, PH19 1AB
details: Open Mon, Tues, Fri, Sat & Sun (Mar– Oct 10.00–18.00) (Nov-Feb 11:00-16:00) Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Coffee Lounge
details: Open Mon-Fri 9:00-16:00, Sat 9:00-14:00. Closed Sun.

name: Cafe 1850
details: Open Mon-Fri 10:00-15:00, Sat,Sun 9:00-14:00. A very nice place, good food and drink. Within the grounds of the Cathedral and enclosed by a wall, so bikes are safe.Indoor and outdoor

name: The Red Telephone Box Tearoom
details: Open Thurs - Sun 11:00 -16:00 Closed Mon-Wed. Indoor and outdoor seating, Nice selection of sandwiches, toasties, cakes and drinks at reasonable prices. Plenty of space and rails outside to lock bikes up to. Apparently can get quite busy so it's worth ringing ahead to book if a group

name: Helwith Tea Garden
address: Manor House Farm, Marske, Helwith, Richmond DL11 7EG
details: Open daily 10:00 -16:00 Outdoor

name: Simply Dutch
details: Open Mon -Sat 9:00-17:00, Sun 10:00-16:00. Funature store with cafe

name: Home Of Feast
address: The Old Chapel, 22 Mill St, Buglawton, Congleton CW12 2AD
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:00 - 1600. Cafe and deli just off the Buxton road in Congleton, Cheshire. Serves a range of snacks and take away items including delicious homemade cakes. Seating upstairs and one small table outside with plenty of room to to lock bikes.

name: The Old Dairy
details: Open Wed 10:00-15:00, Thurs,Fri 9:30-15:00, Sat 9:30-16:00. Closed Sun-Tues. Great food as well as indoor and outdoor seating. Safe places to leave bikes

name: Mobberley Ice Cream farm
address: Dairy Farm, Church Lane, Mobberley WA16 7RA
details: Open Daily from 9:00. -16:00 ish.  No meals but provides drinks, brownies, ice cream, and at weekends scones, Plenty of safe space for bikes, cyclist friendly with track pump, indoor and outdoor seating.

name: Citrus Cafe
details: Open Mon -Sat 10:00 -16:00, Closed Sun. indoor and outdoor seating

name: The Beehive
address: Honey Cottage Caravan Park Selkirk TD7 5HU
details: Open Mon-Fri 10:00-16:00. Excellent cakes, bacon buns and coffee.

name: The Promenade Cafe
details: Open Mon-Fri 10:00-16:30. Sat, Sun 10:00-17:00. Inside and outside seating

name: The Milking Parlour Farm Shop & Cafe
address: Unit 7, Gate Farm, Wettenhall Rd, Nantwich, CW5 6LH
details: Open Mon 9:30 - 15:00, Tues & Fri 9:30 - 17:00, Wed & Thurs 9:30 - 18:30, Sat & Sun 9:00 - 17:00.  Indoor and outdoor seating and secure for bikes. a great place to stop for refreshments & water refills. Indoor and outdoor seating and secure for bikes, Lots of choices of sandwiches and cake, including a gluten free. Breakfasts available all day

name: The Kitchen
address: Main Rd, Wyre Piddle, Pershore WR10 2JB
details: Open Mon, Thurs Fri & Sun 9:00 - 15:00, Tues & Wed 10:00 - 15:00, Sun 9:00 - 15:00. Good food in a beautiful village near the River Avon.

name: Riverside Cafe and Coffee House
details: Open Wed- Sun 11.00 -17.00. Bikes can be taken round to safe back garden, which has a pleasant sitting area by river

name: Jersey Girls Dairy Ice Cream Parlour
address: Higher Woodhill Farm, Woodhill Rd, Bury, BL8 1BS
details: Open daily 11:00 - 17:00. Near Burrs Country Park in Bury. Lovely stop and fabulous ice cream. They also do hot drinks, pies and sausage rolls. Lovely country park and passing classic trains are an added bonus.

name: Shepton Stores Kitchen and Deli
address: Church St, Shepton Beauchamp, Ilminster TA19 0LN
details: Open weekdays 8:30 - 17:00, Sat 8:30 - 15:00, Sun 9:00 - 12:00. A little outdoor seating (go through shop) and can fit maybe 14 cyclists. You have to leave your bikes outside on the very quiet street. There's a little shop as well

name: The Guru Coffee Shop
address: The Old Fenwick Village Hall, Berwick-upon-Tweed TD15 2PJ
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 16:00. Right on NCN Route 1, . Great coffee with a lovely selection of local cakes and savouries. Always a friendly welcome

name: Buon Appetito
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 17:30, Sat 8:00 - 17:00, closed Sun. The food was good and reasonably priced and the staff very friendly. They asked when I went in was if I wanted my water bottles filling.

name: Norse Bakehouse
details: Open daily 10:00 - 15:00 and 17:00 - 21:00 except Thurs when doesn't re-open in the evening.

name: The Barn Tea Room at Rockingham
details: Open Wed - Sun 9:00 - 15:30. Closed Mon & Tues. Great cake selection, friendly staff & great service. Very safe for bikes as the tables are at the back, away from the road and car park. Highly recommended,

name: The Potting Shed
address: Roden Garden Centre, Roden Ln, Roden, Telford TF6 6BP
details: Open Mon - Sat 9:30 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:30. Offers a super menu and a good few cakes. It is accessed via the Garden Centre and has inside and outside seating. There is a low fence between the outside seating and the adjacent grassy area and I would recommend cyclists wheeling their bikes down the pathway and lifting their bikes over that fence to leave them in sight of their seats rather than leave them in the garden.centre car park. Service and food was excellent.

name: The Old Sawmill Cafe
details: Open weekdays 9:30 - 17:30, weekends 9:30 - 16:30. A very smart cafe with lots of outdoor seating and bike racks situated in the beautiful village of Clapham which is on a National Cycle Route. The food is excellent and staff very friendly.

name: Bostock Bakery
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30. Amazing selection of cakes and pastries (incl. perhaps the nicest doughnut I've ever eaten...), some savoury snacks/sandwiches, good coffee (and other drinks). Inside and outside seating, loads of bike parking right outside, a tap for filling water bottles, and bang on NCN 76.

name: Waterfront Cafe
details: Open Wed - Sat 9:00 - 15:00, Sun 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. Good strong coffee, a small but tasty selection of cakes, as well as hot food.  Plenty of room inside, and a few small tables on the pavement outside. No dedicated cycle parking, though there are leaning spaces nearby.

name: The Riverbank
details: Open Tues 9:00 - 16:00, wed - Fri 9:00 - 17:00, Sat 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sun & Mon. Check website as may re-open on Sundays after summer. Indoor / outdoor seating. Coffee & cake, lunches.

name: Roasted Lemon Kiosk
details: Open Sat,Sun 9:30-17:00. Weekdays typically 8:30 -16:30. Outdoor only.

name: Three Trees Cafe
details: Open Tues-Sat 9:30-17:30, Sun 10:00-16:00. Closed Mon. Great farm shop and cafe. Indoor and outdoor seating, bike parking. Coffee, cake, lunches

name: Rye Bakery
details: Open Tues-Sat 8:45-16:00, Sun 10:00-16:00, Closed Mon.

name: The Polly Tea Rooms
details: Open Mon-Sat 8.30-18:00, Sun 9:00-18:00. Amazing selection of biscuits and cakes. Lunches and drinks.

name: The Village Cafe & Takeaway
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 15:00. Terrific cafe, just off the A99 (a possible end to end route) in an otherwise desolate area for such places. New v friendly owners, great breakfast.

name: Jacc's
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:30, Sun 9:30 - 15:30. Great Cafe near the centre of Dunstable. Tables inside and out.  All drinks £1* and very good value menu (e.g. drink & sandwich & cake £4.95 at 19/06/2023.)

name: The Old Post Office Cafe
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 15:00. Closed Mon - Wed. Outside seating if needed. Simple and excellent lunches, good cakes.

name: Pick's Barn
address: North Luffenham Road, Lyndon, Oakham, LE15 8TY
details: Open Tues -Sat 9:00 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00, closed Mon. Indoor and outdoor seating, the latter with terrifiic views across the Chater Valley. Very welcoming to cyclists but, if the group is large (10+), it would be wise to call in advance. Now has loads or proper bike parking installed.

name: Roast & Radish
details: Open Wed-Sun 10.00 -1500  Snacks and drinks. Outdoor seating only.

name: Antlers Cafe and Bistro
details: Open daily 8:00 -20:00. Breakfast, lunch, cakes/ice cream and dinner, plus takeaways a couple of nights a week Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Craigard Kitchen
address: Miners Row, Ballygrant, Isle of Islay PA45 7QR
details: Open Wed-Sat 10:00-16:00, and very cyclist friendly. A couple of picnic tables outside and plenty of tables indoors . A good lunch menu and the cakes are delicious!

name: Beez Kneez Cafe
details: Open Mon, Wed - Fri - 9:00-15:00, Sat-Sun 8:30 -15:00, Closed Tues, Small grooups about 10 seats inside and similar outside.Close to tow path.

name: Riverbank kiosk
details: Open daily 10:00-16:00. Outdoor only. Toasties and cakes, hot and cold drinks.

name: The Shepherds Baa
details: Drinks, cakes, ice cream and sandwiches.  Lots of outside tables, some under cover There is a customer toilet.

name: Rise and Flour Artisan Bakery & Cafe
address: The Elms, Shipton Rd, Milton-under-Wychwood, Chipping Norton OX7 6JW
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:30 - 14:30, Sat & Sun 9:00 - 14:30. Nice cafe with plenty of space for bikes.

name: Quarters Coffee
address: Unit 1, Glen Avon House, Millennium Walk, Newport NP19 0LZ
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00, closed Sun. Mostly outside seating (a couple of tables sheltered) but you can sit inside and see your bikes leaning on something outside.

name: Cornerstone Cafe
details: Open Tues - Thurs 10:00 - 14:00. Bike parking across the street. Cyclists are very welcome as the volunteers like to chat and hear our stories.  At present it is 'only' serving tea/coffee and cake, but what great homemade cakes!  Evanton is on the 'Coach Road' to Alness, a bigger town.

name: The Cowshed at Hadfer Glamping
details: Hot food counter & seating open daily 12:00 - 16:00 Sun - Thurs, 12:00 - 17:00 Fri & Sat,. Takeaway open 8:00 - 20:00. There’s a bike rack on the car park too. They served freshly made toasted paninis and a wide range of Welsh pasties as finger food for a more chilled out pit stop. The range of “Rediculously Rich” cakes are great too. It’s not open for breakfasts as the cowshed is used by HADFER Glamoing for their bed and breakfast guests but it is hoped that breakfast baps will be available soon.

name: Tea on the beach
address: Inverlussa Beach, Ardlussa, Isle of Jura, PA60 7XW
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00 (Summer Only) An unstaffed horesebox trailer with daily fresh cakes and a hot water flask for teas and coffees. It operates an honesty box system, and is a welcome refreshment stop if you're pedalling up and down the Long Road on the island.

name: Clara's Cocina
address: Guards’ Polo Club, Smiths Lawn, Windsor Great Park, TW20 0HP
details: Open mid April - mid September)  9:00 - 16:00 daily

name: Halton Tennis Centre
address: Chestnut End, Halton Village, Halton, Aylesbury HP22 5PD
details: Open weekdays from 9:15 - 20:30, Sat 8:30 - 18:30, Sun 10:00 - 16:00. Best to check website as times vary summer - winter. Coffee and cake, plus light lunches. Indoor and outdoor seating, loos, bike racks. It’s not that obvious it’s open to all. Signed tennis centre off Chestnut Avenue.

name: The Squires Pantry at Felbrigg Hall
details: Open 10:00 - 16:30 when the Hall is open (10:00 - 15:30 in Winter). Cafe, toilets and right on the Rebellion Way. You don’t have to pay entry to use Cafe.

name: Muddy Boots Cafe at Bickling Hall
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00 (10:00 - 15:00 in Winter)

name: The Flying Goose Coffee Shop
address: Six Hills Ln, Six Hills, Loughborough LE14 3PR
details: Open Mon, Wed, Fri & Sat 9:00-15:00, Tues 16:30-20:00  Thurs 11:00-20:00, Sun 10:00-13:00. Newly refurbished with lovely lake views. Hot and cold food and drinks, plenty of seating inside and outside

name: Oscars Cafe
address: Easterton Farm Park, Craigallian Rd, Mugdock G62 8LG
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Good coffee, cakes, hot and cold food, all day breakfasts etc. Handy for cycling in Mugdock and not far off John Muir Way.

name: Mocha Jak's Coffee Shop
address: Geilsland Estate, Geilsland Rd, Beith KA15 1HD
details: Open Tues - Sun 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon. Good Coffee, food, cakes, seating inside and out and bike parking.

name: Sour Cow
details: Open Tues - Sat 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sun & Mon. Nice little cafe with court yard behind (down alley) to park bikes.

name: The Old Post Office Shop
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00. Has a lovely garden as well as indoor seating. On Sustrans route 41.

name: Kemerton Coffee House
details: Open Mon & Tues 8:30 - 15:00, Wed & Fri 8:30 - 16:00, Thurs 8:30 - 16:30, weekends 9:00 - 16:00. Sells interesting sandwiches, cakes and has specials as main meals. Next to The Crown pub.

name: Cafe Afloat
details: Open Wed - Sun 9:00 - 15:30, closed Mon & Tues. in a canal barge in Worcester next to the River Severn is a great place to stop. Has outside seating and a canopy for hot or wet weather. Sells coffees, sandwiches etc.

name: The Golden Larches
address: Balquhidder Station, Uam Vaar, Lochearnhead FK19 8NX
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00, closed Tues.

name: Wildflower Cafe
address: West Bagborough Rd, Cothelstone, Taunton TA4 3DU
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 15:15, closed Mon - Wed. Outdoor seating with some undercover seating. Very friendly.

name: Sandpipers
details: Open Mon, Thurs, Fri 10:00-16:00, Sat,Sun 9:30-16:30. Great coffee and other drinks, cakes & savouries.Inside and Outside. Small but very friendly and welcoming.

name: Ashbury Tea Room & Shop
details: Open Tues-Sat !0:00-14:30 Closed Sun, Mon Close to Ridgewat

name: The Walkin
details: Open Summer daily  9:00-16:00.Winter Wed- Sun 9:00-16:00 Good range of Coffee and Cakes , light lunches , chilled drinks including bottled beers

name: Court Hill Centre
address: Court Hill Rd, Letcombe Regis, Wantage OX12 9NE
details: Open daily 10:30 - 16:00 (16:30 on weekends). 4 Kms south of Wantage just off the A338 and the Ridgeway. A good place to stop for basic hostel style accommodation and food. The Ridgeway has very few cafes and this one is only 0.5 km off the route. Cafe does sandwiches, toasties, baked potatoes and soup.

name: Brookhouse Farm Shop & Cafe
address: Wilmslow Road, Mottram ST Andrew, Cheshire, SK10 4QY
details: Open Mon-Sat 8:00 -17:30, Sun 9:00-16:30. Inside and outside seating. Bike racks

name: The Railway Carriage
address: Waltham Windmill, Brigsley Rd, Waltham, Grimsby DN37 0JZ
details: Open Sat& Sun 10:00-16:00 Closed Weekdays.

name: Flootes
address: 18 Market Place, Woburn, Milton Keynes MK17 9PZ
details: Open Mon - Fri 8:00 - 17:00, Sat - Sun 9:00 - 17:00

name: Forum Speciality Coffee
details: Open Mon-Fri 8:00-18:00, Sat 9:00-16:00, Sun 9:00-15:00.A little small inside, only  coffee and cake at the moment, some outside seating

name: Wood Street Bakery
address: Inside Metro Food Centre, Wood St, London E17 3JX
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00. Sun 8:00 - 15:00. Great place to stop off after rides in West Essex/Epping. Great coffee and delicious selection of sweet and savoury pastries.  Great coffee and delicious selection of sweet and savoury pastries.

name: The Neathouse
details: Open Mon-Fri 9:00-16:00, Sat 8:00-16:00, Sun 10:00-15:00. About ten cosy seats inside, some picnic tables on the green outside. Good selection of cakes and savouries.  Hot and cold drinks available

name: Chain Bridge Honey Farm Cafe Bus
address: Horncliffe, Berwick upon Tweed, Northumberland, TD15 2XT
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00 - 16:00 (closed Mondays and Tuesdays including bank holidays) from April to October. Seats in or outside the bus, good cake and scone choice, also sandwiches etc. Some outside seating is undercover, can park bike nearby.

name: The Loft Cafe and Bakery
details: Open Mon - Sat 9:00 - 16:00, closed Sun. Tucked away off the main road, large first floor cafe but outside courtyard seating and sheffield stands just opposite. Coffee, tea, cakes, scones, lunches etc, also a take away shop.

name: Cafe Filly
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sun. Use the Cockenzie House garden entrance to access the Cafe. Good scones and cakes, lunches looked nice too. Was quite busy so drawback might be difficulty in getting a table at populat times! Covered bike rack (wheel benders) but probably reasonably safe leaving bikes in the garden anyway, poster on wall said bike repair kit and pump available on request.

name: Dandelion and Duck
details: Open Wed - Sat 9:00-16:00, Sun  10:00-14:00 Closed Mon, Tues Excellent menu, coffee and cakes.  Cycle racks soon.  More seating at the rear.

name: Alfrick Community shop and cafe
details: Open Mon-Fri 9:00-17:00, Sat,Sun 9:00-12:00

name: No.19 Cafe
details: Open daily 8:00-17:00, Breakfasts, cakes, sandwiches. Friendly, fairly small

name: Itteringham Community Shop & Cafe
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:15-16:45, Sun 9:15-16:00 Idoor and some outdoor seating. Basic tools and pump available

name: Yum Yums
details: Open Sun-Thurs 8:00-17, Sat 8:00-23:00, sun 8:00-15:00Limited outdoor seating

name: Sevenoaks Garden Centrre Cafe
address: Plot 16, Lon Parcwr Ind Est, Ruthin LL15 1NJ
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:00-17:30, Sun 9:00-17:00Indoor and Outdoor seating. Bike parking

name: Manons Riverside Cafe
address: National Whitewater Centre, Fron-goch, Bala LL23 7NU
details: Open daily 9:00-16:00 Indoor and Outdoor seating

name: Bocs Bwyd
details: Open  Wed-Fri 8:00-15:00, Sat 9:00-15:00, Sun 10:00-15:00. Indoor aand Outdoor seating.

name: Fernhurst Hub
details: Mon,Tues,Thur,Fri 10:00 -16:00, Wed 10:00-13:00, Sat 10:00-12:00 Indoor and outdoor seating. Hot & cold drinks and snacks

name: Camphill Cafe
address: Japonica Lane, Willen Park, Milton Keynes, MK15 9JY
details: Lovely vegetarian cafe run by learning disability adults . Open Mon-Fri 10:00-16:00, Closed Sat,Sun.Indoor and outside seating.

name: Cholmondeley Farm Shop and Cafe
address: 10 Bickerton Road, Cholmondeley nr Malpas SY14 8AQ
details: Open Tues-Fri 9:00-17:00, ,Sat,sun 9:00-15:00, Closed Mon. Great cafe. Coffee and cake recommended,

name: Maggie's
details: Open Tues-Sat 9:00-21:00, Sun 10:00-15:00, Mon 9:00-16:00. Very friendly. Room for bikes.Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Chirbury Cafe and shop
details: Open Mon-Fri 8:00-14:30, Sat 8:00-15:00, Sun 9:00-12:00 (breakfasts only) Small Cafe at the rear of the shop with outdoor area. Bikes can be left at the front of the shop in view of shop staff.it is a quite area but better to have a cafe lock.

name: Toll Bar Cottage Cafe
details: Open Tue, Thurs-Sat 10:00-14:00. Closed Wed,Sun,Mon.

name: Pacific Garden Centre
address: Chester Road, Streetly, Aldridge, West Midlands, WS9 0PH
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:00-16:30, Sun 10:00-16:00 No real bike parking, but some wall space or the guard rail on the entrance screen.Typical garden centre cafe, about 100 seats inside, 40 outside.Normal range of hot and cold food and drinks.

name: Castle Cottage Cafe
details: Open Tues- Sat 8:30-16:00  Ample space to park bikes  accessed via  Market Place.  you may have t walk through on market days ( Wes,Sat) Can be busy, but you can book a table (or two) in advance.

name: The Carriage at Kislingbury Sunnies & Spooks.
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:30 throughout the year but check website in winter as times may change. a converted 1940s railway carriage serving coffee/ tea, cold drinks, panini's, cakes, brownies and other sweet treats. There is a serving hatch specifically for people not within the PYO field so the entry fee is not payable to just use the cafe. Also has outdoor seating.

name: Honesty Cafe at Tally Ho Farm
details: Open Mon - Sat 8:30 - 16:30, Sun 10:00 - 16:00. Cakes, Breakfast Baps, Salads, Ice Cream hot and cold drinks

name: Pie & Pickle
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00.

name: Glen Lyon Coffee Roasters
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16:00, closed weekends.  Rather decent Orange Polenta Cake. Chilled feel to the sitting area with some light soulful jazz in the air.

name: Cafe Gerlan
address: Inigo Jones Slate Museum, Y Groeslon, Caernarfon, Gwynedd LL54 7UE
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:00-16:00. Breakfasts & lunches with ingredients from  local farm. Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: Yellow Hare Cafe
address: Gott Pier, Scarinish , Isle of Tiree. PA77 6TN
details: Open Mon,Thus,Fri 10:00-16:00. Tues 10:00-18:00, Sat 9:00-18:00, Sun 12:00-16:00.Right beside the ferry terminal for coffee, cake, dagels and breakfast rolls. Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: Scarinish Beach Hotel
details: The hotel has a bar servicing walkers, cyclists, windsurfers, stravaigers with excellent food, snacks and drinks to suit your needs.

name: Foodie's Emporium
