details: Open Tues - Fri 8:45 - 15:00, Sat 8:30 - 15:00, close Sun & Mon.  Handful of tables inside, but has a fair few seats outside, so you can keep an eye on your bike. Lovely home made cakes and savoury options such as Scott eggs and salads. Their brie and bacon baps are stunning as well.

name: Time at the Forge
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30, Sat 10:00 - 16:30, closed Sun. Stunning and cosy little cafe, lovely outdoor eating area, where you can park your bikes, and inside is really nice as well. Really friendly owner and staff, coffee is really good, and the cakes and scones are fantastic.

name: Aldbourne Post office cafe & deli
details: Open weekdays 7:30 - 18:00, Sat 7:30 - 16:00. closed Sun. If you pop in and ask they will open up a door at the side so you can wheel your bike through to a secure back garden - they have seating outside and inside if the weather is not being kind.Great freshly made sandwiches, hot food including soups, and lovely cakes and sweet treats - good range of hot drinks too.

name: Priscillas Kitchen
address: Back St, East Garston, Hungerford RG17 7EX
details: Open Wed - Sat 10:00 - 15:00, closed Sun - Tues. Stunning hot and cold food, really nice scrambled eggs, coffee and cakes are also fantastic. Fair bit of outdoor seating, plenty of indoor seating, and ample place for bikes.

name: Herdwicks Cafe
details: Open Mon - Fri 10:00 - 17:00, weekends 9:00 - 17:00. Turn up on your bike and you'll get 10 % off.

name: Courtyard Tea Rooms
address: Hall Farm, Collingham Rd, Newton on Trent, Lincoln LN1 2LL
details: Open Tues - Fri 9:30 - 15:00, closed Sat - Mon. Tucked away from the road, good food and drink. Entry is from the A1133.

name: Bledington Community Shop and Cafe
address: Church St, Bledington, Chipping Norton OX7 6XB
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, Sun 9:00 - 13:00. Some indoor seating, more outside and in the marquee.

name: Riseley Village Tea Room
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 12:00. Based in the Memorial Hall. Very welcoming and traditional.

name: The Velo Barn
address: Unit 1, Betsoms Farm, Pilgrims Way, Westerham TN16 2DS
details: Open Tues - Fri 8:00 - 17:00, Sat & Sun 9:00 - 13:00.

name: Northycote Farm Tearooms
details: Open Tues-Sun 10:00-15:30.Closed Mon except Bank Hols. and School Hols. Good selection (and portions) of cake, savouries, hot and cold sandwiches and light meals. About 20 seats inside, about the same outside.

name: Seven Districts Coffee Roasters
address: Nettleham Community Hub, 1 East St, Nettleham, Lincoln LN2 2SL

name: Jo-Co Cafe
address: The Forge Garage, Handcross, Haywards Heath RH17 6BJ
details: Open daily 7:30 - 16:30, Sun 8:00 - 16:00, closed Mon.Small cafe with an upstairs. Always busy with cyclists on weekend. Nice coffee, good homemade cake - pastel de nata the speciality and an alley by the side perfect for bikes.

name: Little Milton Village Shop and Post Office
address: Thame Rd, Little Milton, Oxford OX44 7PZ
details: Open daily 8:30 - 17:30, Sun 9:00 - 12:30. Great cakes, and snacks such as bacon rolls, sausage rolls etc. Good price too. Also, tables outside round the back as well, which is great in summer

name: Torksey Lock
address: Lock Row, Torksey Lock, Lincoln LN1 2EH
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:00-16:00. Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: The Nook
address: 40A High St, Markyate, St Albans AL3 8PA
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 9:30 - 15:00. Food excellent, lovely interior and toilets spotless.  Highly recommended.

name: The Grain Store
details: Open weekdays 8:30 - 16:00, Sat & Sun 10:00 - 16:00. It's not easy to spot as the cafe signs are not particularly large and it's pretty much hidden by what used to be chicken sheds. Hot food served until 2:30PM

name: Joey's Cafe
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:30 indoor and outdoor seating Vegan food is available

name: Ginger & Pickles
details: Open Mon-Thurs 9:00-16:00, Fri 9:00-16:30, Sat 9:00-17:00, Sun 10:00-16:00. Indoor and outdoor seating Bakery oposite for takeaways.

name: Pickleberry Coffee and Gift Shop
details: Open Tues-Fri 10:00 -15:00.Saturday 10:00 -14:00. indoor and outdoor seating. Fences to lean the bike against.

name: Gather Cafe
address: The Ennerdale Centre, Ennerdale Bridge, Cleator CA23 3AR

name: Loading Bay Cafe
address: Kardleton House, Vansittart Estate, Windsor SL4 1SE
details: Open Thurs & Fri 9:00 - 13:30, Sat 9:00 - 14:00. Closed Sun - Wed

name: Waterside Café
details: Open Mon-Sun 8:00 - 15:00

name: Blue Tin Coffee Bar
address: Keepers Cottage, Garsons Farm, Ipsden OX10 6QU
details: Open Wed - Sat 9:00 - 15:00, closed Sun - Tues

name: Casual Kitchen @ Lyme Breeze
details: Open Tues - Sun 11:00 - 16:00

name: The Cake Shack
address: Cudmore Fisheries, The Pleck, Whitmore, Newcastle Under Lyme, ST5 5HU
details: Open Wed & Thurs 10:00 - 15:00, Fri 10:00 - 15:30, Sat & Sun  10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. The best cake and the widest choice of cake. There is hot food too. You look out on the fishing lakes and the benches must be lovely in the summer. The people are friendly and welcoming. Only one loo with a sticking door so don’t panic that you are trapped. No cycle racks but it’s nowhere near a main road so no worries propping bikes with a cafe lock.

name: Nineteeen Cafe Bar
details: Open 8:30 - 15:30, closed Sun. Breakfast, lunch, coffee & cake, bike racks opposite.

name: Bird in Bush Inn & Coffee Shop
address: Village Green, Elsdon, Newcastle upon Tyne NE19 1AA
details: Open daily 9:00 - late. Outdoor seating in the beer garden.

name: Leila’s Foodhut
address: South Cliff Road, Kirton in Lindsey DN21 4NP

name: The Bull & Butcher
address: Common Ln, Corley Moor, Coventry CV7 8AQ
details: Open daily from 9:00. Breakfasts 9:00 - 11:00 - Mon - Sat, 9:00 - 10:30 Sun. Good breakfasts, friendly staff, outdoor seating too, including sheltered booths.

name: The Lamppost
address: Burrs Country Park, Woodhill Rd, Bury BL8 1DA
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00.

name: Base Coffee + Kitchen
address: Long Crendon Manor Stables, Thame Rd, Long Crendon, Aylesbury HP18 9FF
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30, Sun 10:00 - 15:00. Super friendly with great coffee and food.

name: First Light Coffee
details: Open daily 7:30 - 15:30. Run by cyclists and runners, bike storage, great coffee, cakes and food, great friendly staff, indoor and outdoor seating. Right on the Taff Trail, bike shop next door.

name: Barbarella
details: Open daily 9:00-17:00 Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Leaf and Ground
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00. Good food both indoors and out with plenty of seating. No bike racks, but a handy drainpipe you can lock your bike to.

name: The Well
address: 46 East Green, West Auckland, Bishop Auckland DL14 9HJ
details: Open Wed - Fri 10:00 - 15:00, closed Sat - Tues. Very welcoming community Cafe with great coffee and homemade soup and cakes. I was on a solo ride, and had a lovely chat with one of the ladies working there - they seem to be deliberately overstaffed so they have time to do this!

name: Crichton Central
address: Crichton Central The Crichton Estate, Bankend Rd, Dumfries DG1 4TA
details: Open daily 9:00 – 16:00  Definitely cycle friendly, stone's throw from NCN 7. There is a covered bike rack area and a long fence that bikes can be locked to. Also has outdoor tables and a covered terrace.

name: Brockley Stores Farm Shop
details: Open Mon - Thurs 8:00 - 17:00, Fri & Sat 8:00 - 18:00, Sun 9:00 - 17:00. Has outside seating only. Coffee, cakes, fruit and other deli foods. On the A370 which is a busy road, but a good stop off. Toilets available.

name: Coffee n’ Cones
address: Downs Banks - Ford, Wash Dale Lane, Stone ST15 8UU
details: Open Fri 10:00 - 15:00, Sat & Sun 10:00 - 16:30. A smashing little place with great coffee, cakes and snacks. Outdoor seating.

name: Hoar park craft village and farm
address: Hoar Park Farm, Ansley, Nuneaton CV10 0QU
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon. Summer/School Holidays: Mon - Sun 10:00 - 16:00

name: Woodview Farm Shop & Cafe
details: Open daily 8:30 - 17:00. Sat 8:30 - 16:00, Sun 9:00 - 13:00. Indoor and outdoor seating - you have to walk through the farm shop to access the Cafe at the rear. Seems popular - the farm shop was very busy during our visit and a lot of the indoor tables were reserved.

name: Winners Tea Rooms & Terrace
address: The Green, Finchingfield, Braintree, Essex, CM7 4JX
details: Open Mon, Wed-Fri 9:00-16:00, Sat & Sun 9:00-16:00. Can be very busy on Sundaywith cyclists and motorcyclists as the Pcture Pot tearoom is closed Sun.  Indoor and outdoor seating is available (if you are lucky!) but customers are still served on the grassed area outside the shop. Good choice of food, cakes and hot drinks.

name: Roots Cafe
address: Blackthorpe Barns, Rougham, Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, IP30 9HZ
details: Open daily 9:00-16:00Indoor or outdoor seating.  Wheel bender racks but plenty of timber fences.

name: Wave
address: Washingpool Farm, Main Road, Easter Compton, Bristol, BS35 5RE
details: Open Thurs- Sun 6:00 - 2030. Please check website for seasonal changes

name: Petit Yellow Vélo
details: Take away  coffee and cake only Open Wed-Sat 9:00-14:00

name: Gift Cafe
details: Open daily  10:00-16:00. Indoor and nice outdoor seating, Bike rack

name: Victor Victoria Coffee
details: Open Mon-Sat 8:30-15:00, Sun 9:00 -14:00. Bike racks at front. Extensive indoor seating and about 4 tables at the front. A variety of meals/snacks, a good selection of cakes,

name: Cafe @ Lock 81
address: Bothchworth Lock House, 99 Church St, Rickmansworth WD3 1JJ
details: Open Wed - Sun 10:30 - 17:30, closed Mon & Tues. Open Bank Holidays. Small outdoor kiosk serving hot & cold drinks, breakfast baps and snacks. Outdoor seating by the canal

name: The Secret Valley Catering box
details: Open Fri - Sun 10:00 - 16:00

name: The Little Coffee Shop & Chocolate Co
address: The Stables, High Melton, Doncaster DN5 7SZ
details: Open Fri-Sun 8:30-15:00. Indoor & Outdoor seating. Fabulous coffee and homemade cakes and sandwiches. Bikes can go in the courtyard so stay in view.

name: Tŵr Marcwis Anglesey Column
details: Site is accessed via Parc Twr, off Lôn Pant in Llanfairpwll, don’t go in via the main visitor car park otherwise you’ll be carrying your bike up some steps hike’a’bike style. Open daily  9:00-17:00

name: The Lodge Cafe
details: Open Thurs-Mon 9:00-14:00, closed Tues,Wed. Indoor and outdoor seating

name: The Hub & Spoke
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 13:00. very good coffee and snacking. Bike parking covered by CCTV and they’ll provide locks too. Inside is well laid out, charge points everywhere. It’s also a hot desking and meeting space, ideal 3rd space if you’re WFH. Location is Melton Road but you need to go to the right of the church next door or round the end nearest the crossing to access the car park at the rear and the cycle parking.

name: Ardnamurchan lighthouse Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:30 April - October, check website for other times. Indoor and outdoor seating. Toilets. Copious amount of tea with hot water. Tasty variety of cakes. They had WiFi available.

name: Lordington Park Tea Rooms
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 15:00.

name: Spencer’s
address: Newsham Grange, South Otterington , Northallerton, DL7 9JE

name: Gypsy Cream Cafe Shop
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:30, closed Sun & Mon. Award winning tea rooms, great food and drink and very friendly staff.

name: Bridge Cottage Art Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Wed & Thurs.

name: Eddy's Cafe & Bar
address: Hillend Caravan Park, Hillend, Llangennith, Swansea SA3 1JD
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16:00, weekends 9:00 - 18:00. Really good breakfast here. Good selection of food and drink, comfortable, and friendly staff.

name: Palmerston's
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, Sun 11:00 - 16:00. Excellent lunches, great variety, including V and Vg.

name: Woodford Halse Community Cafe
address: School St, Woodford Halse, Daventry NN11 3RL
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:00 - 15:00, closed Sun & Mon.

name: The Pavilion Bar And Restaurant
details: Open daily 9:00 - 23:30. The food was good & very reasonably priced (£5.95 for a sausage bap & americano 17/05/24) & the service was excellent.  They were very happy for me to share their details & look forward to seeing other cycling groups.  Please give them a courtesy call to let them know of numbers & expected time of arrival to help them out.

name: The Salt Cellars Cafe
details: Open Mon 10:00 - 16:00, Tues - Thurs 9:00 - 18:00, Fri & Sat 9:00 - 22:00, Sun 10:00 - 14:00. Seating inside and out, friendly staff, good food & drinks. Good visibility of bikes if sat inside.

name: Eduardo's Pizzeria and Cafe
details: Open Mon,Tues, Thurs-Sat. 9:00-17:00 (Pizzeria until 21:00) Sun 10:00-16:00 Closed Wed.Good food cakes. Welcomes cyclists. Safe to bring bikes through the cafe.Outdoor courtyard

name: Milepost Cafe
address: Spen Valley Greenway, Liversage, W Yorkshire WF15 6PS
details: Indoor and outdoor seating or takeaway. Hot and cold drinks. Hot bacon rolls etc

name: Three Crown's Tea Shop
details: Open Mon-Fri 9:00-16:00, Sat 9:00-15:00, Closed SunIndoor and outdoor seating

name: The Ugly Mug Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:30 / 16:00. Indoor and outdoor seating. Bike parking adjacent, great foods and friendly staff.

name: Oakley Village Stores
details: un 1Open Mon-Fri 8:30 -16:30 (Wed closes13:00) Sat 9:00-13:00, Sun 11:30-13:30 Limited indoor space but outside tables, coffee and cakes/pastries

name: Grinders Coffee Shop
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00.

name: Jack Rabbits
details: Open Tues - Sat 8:30 - 16:00, Sun & Mon 10:00 - 16:00. Good breakfast and lunch menu and all important cake selection with friendly staff. Lots of indoor and outdoor seating with space outside to prop bikes up and keep an eye on them. Located off the road, it’s accessible via an alleyway near Costa or from the car park at the back but beware the one way system.

name: Pound Farm Cafe
details: Open Tues, Wed & Sat 10:00 - 16:00, Thurs & Fri 10:00 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00, closed Mon. Fabulous coffee, breakfasts and cakes.

name: Bean Theory
address: Waresley Park Estate, Gamlingay Rd, Waresley, Sandy SG19 3DD
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:00. Extensive outdoor seating in the very pleasant, almost triangular-shaped courtyard formed by the stable buildings. There is a cycle rack (rail) for several bikes by the entrance to the courtyard; under the eaves of the southern building there is a cycle maintenance station comprising several captive tools (on cables) and a track pump. The coffee shop even has a small selection of SiS energy gels (together with a choice of the locally roasted coffee to fill your saddlebag with).

name: Cafe Needles Eye
address: Hurst Road, Milford - On - Sea, Lymington, SO41 0PY
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Great view, breakfasts and coffee.

name: Elsie May's
details: Open daily 8:00 - 17:00, closed Sun. An excellent coffee and fine breakfast stop if doing the Tiverton Canal ride. Wonderful cakes with great service.

name: Lagg Distillery
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00.  (Summer opening, check website for winter hours)A great cafe and particularly welcome since some other places have closed on the west coast of Arran

name: Laughing Duck Cafe
details: Open daily 9:30-16:00. Excellent cafe and lots of cyclists use it

name: The Old Butchers
details: Open Mon, Wed-Fri 8:00-16:00,  Sat/Sun 10:00-16:00, closed Tues, Superb cycle friendly cafe serving cakes, sandwiches, pancakes, soups, scones and pastries. indoor and outdoor (covered) seating

name: Kington Cafe
details: Open Tues - Sat 9:00 - 15:00, closed Sun & Mon. Run by a fellow cyclist, fab food, friendly service & highly recommended

name: Cafe 1756
address: The Dudley Arms, Ingleby Greenhow, Great Ayton, Middlesbrough TS9 6LL
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Many local cycling groups use it as an end of ride or mid ride stop. If busy, service can be slow at times, but the quality of the food on offer is excellent.

name: Sanwitches Cafe
address: Union mill, Watt St, Sabden, Clitheroe BB7 9ED
details: Open daily 9:00 - 14:00, closed Mon & Tues. A cracking friendly cafe at the foot of Pendle Hill in the lovely Ribble Valley.  Great value and service.

name: The Highlanders Bakehouse
details: Open Thurs - Sun 10:00 - 16:00, closed Mon - Wed. Amazing bakehouse. Excellent Coffee. Just lots and lots of good, tasty calories- the problem was the incredible range of choice. Indoor/outdoor seating.

name: Wild Blackberry Cafe
address: Swanns Nursery, Eyke Rd, Bromeswell, Woodbridge IP12 2PN
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:30, Sun 10:00 - 15:30. A good cafe for cyclists with bike rack and outdoor/indoor seating.

name: The Boathouse
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, Sat & Sun 9:00 - 17:00.In an old chandlers shop at Uphill Marina. Ideally located at the start of the off road cycle route from Weston to Burnham, at the foot of Uphill Quarry. Indoor and Outdoor seating, great location, good range of food and drinks plus an outdoor ice cream stall.

name: Forsinard Lodge
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed all Nov, Dec - Mar close Wed & Thurs. Cycle parking indoor and outdoor seating.  Welcoming hosts. Cafe and B&B in the middle of nowhere.

name: The Midge Bite Cafe
details: Open Wed - Sat 8:00 - 17:00, Sun 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon. In the middle of nowhere at Achnasheen a welcome respite for anyone touring across country in Scotland.

name: Synge & Byrne Slieve Gullion
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Very friendly staff serving a nice selection of coffees, cakes & savoury food. Indoor & outdoor seating, toilets in the nearby car park. Near the car park for the forest park and just before the start of the forest drive. Make sure you fuel up well for the selection of 17 - 20% climbs. Once you start there's no turning back - it's a one way road.

name: The Birdhouse Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 15:00, Sat 9:30 - 14:30, closed Sun. Small Cafe with indoor & outdoor seating. Doesn’t look much from the road, but is a real gem!

name: The Greenbean Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 14:30, weekends 10:00 - 14:00, closed Mon. A small, but perfectly well formed cafe with indoor & outdoor seating. Cyclists always welcome.

name: Courtyard Restaurant & Coffee Shop
address: Brogdale Farm House, Brogdale Rd, Faversham ME13 8XZ
details: Open Tues -Sun 10:00-16:00 Closed Mon  Spacious courtyard.

name: Katy's Bakes @ The Reading Room
details: Open Tues -Fri 10:00-16:00 Limited  space inside but the church and park opposite have plenty of seats. Good coffee and excellent cakes as well as breakfasts and lunches. Best to book

name: Flint Barn Cafe
address: Whitlingham Country Park, Whitlingham Lane, Norwich. NR14 8TR
details: Open daily 9:00-17:00 A few cycle stands and plenty of outdoor seating.

name: Vatersay Hall Cafe
address: Castlebay, Eilean Sair, Isle of Barra HS9 5YW
details: Summer Open Daily 10:00-16:00 See Facebook for reduced opening hours out of season

name: Karelia House Cafe
address: Karelia House Yarn and Fabric, , Kenmore Road, Comrie Bridge By Aberfeldy PH15 2LS
details: Open Wed - Sat 10:00 - 16:00, closed Sun - Tues. Nice cafe in Yarn & Fabric Shop. Outside (covered) seating with plenty of space for bikes. Selection of hot/cold drinks, cakes and light lunches. Indoor/outdoor seating. - Outdoor seating (covered).

name: Salthouse Store
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:00, Sun 8:30 - 13:00. Limited seating inside but benches outside & on the green

name: Highland Fold Ice Cream
details: Open Wed - Sun 11:00 - 17:00 April - Oct. Scrumptious highland cow homemade ice cream and lots of teas, coffees , cakes and puddings. Outside in the garden and inside seating (in a barn). Just a few hundred yards off route 78 cycleway ( up glen salachan on road towards Bonawe and turn right). Great for cyclists, a locals’ secret.

name: Caffi'r Sgwar
details: Open Mon -Sat 9:00-16:00, sun 10:00-16:00  Tasty breakfasts, rolls, lunches, great cake selection. Friendly service.  Indoor 8 tables, and outdoor seating.

name: Ferry Cabin
details: Open Fri-Sat 10:00 – 19:30, Sun  10:00 - 14:30 Great coffee, sandwiches, home made cakes, ice cream. Friendly service.  Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: The Rook house cafe
details: Open Tues-Sat 10:00-17:00  Sun 10:00-15:00  Closed Mon. Indoor and outdoor seating  Next to the pub

name: Denver Mill cafe
details: Open Thurs-Sun 10:00-16:00. Old Mill complex courtyard.. Cakes to die for all made on site.

name: Nevillery Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00-17:00 No entry fee

name: Sharnbrook Deli Cafe
details: Open Mon 8:00 - 14:30, Tues - Fri 8:00 - 15:00, Sat 9:00 - 14:00, closed Sun. They have a nice garden at the back to use and allows you to put your bikes safely there.

name: The Yurt Cafe
address: The Cricketers on the Green, The Grn, Pirbright, Woking GU24 0JT
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Located in the pub beer garden. Bike parking between the yurt and awning at the back. Seating indoors and out, with great cake and coffee.

name: Imma The Bakery
address: Unit 51, Van Alloys Industrial Estate, Busgrove Ln, Stoke Row, Henley-on-Thames RG9 5QW
details: Open Wed - Sat 8:00 - 14:00, Sun 8:00 - 13:00. Closed Mon & Tues for cake,  pastries, sarnies and hot drinks. Benches outside for seating.

name: Church Farm Cafe
address: Church Farm, Station Rd, Aldbury, HP23 5RS
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:00. Cycling themed Cafe also selling cycling merchandise, run by cycling enthusiasts.

name: St Ninians Tearoom
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:30. Plenty of seating indoors and some outdoors. Bikes can be left in the outside area, visible from the cafe. We only had coffee and cake, but I think they do meals too. It’s on the Machars Red Cycle route - a 22 mile circular route.

name: One Market Street Cafe
details: Open Tues, Thurs - Sat 9:00 - 16:00, Wed 9:00 - 14:30, closed Sun & Mon. On route 27 ,Tarka Trail

name: The Loose Box Cafe
details: Open daily 9:30 - 15:00, closed Mon & Sun. Nice location with the backdrop of the Malvern hills, and serve great cakes, have gluten free options.  Think they also do lunches aswell.  Inside and outside seating.

name: Granite Way Cycles Cafe
address: The Goods Shed, The Youth Hostel, Klondyke Rd, Okehampton EX20 1EW
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00 April - Oct, 9:00 - 15:00 Nov - Mar. Opposite Okehampton station. Have e.bike charging facilities.

name: Franklin's Dairy Cafe
address: Trumpetons Farm, Thorncote Green, Sandy SG19 1PU
details: Open Mon - Tues 9:00 - 16:00, Wed - Fri 8:30 - 17:00, Sat 8:30 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00.  Seating inside and out. Plenty of space for bikes. Great service and range.

name: The Hive
address: 11 South Cres, Garlieston, Newton Stewart DG8 8BQ
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:00, closed Wed. Good breakfasts, lunches, coffee and hot drinks, nice cakes too.

name: Wigeon Cafe
address: WWT Welney Hundred Foot Bank Welney Norfolk PE14 9TN
details: FREE to enter cafe/visitor centre. Open daily 9:00-16:00 Summer Thursa until 20:00. happy to keep bikes secure, Indoor and outdoor seating. fantastic first floor views over wetland habitat

name: O'Brennans
address: Great Walsingham Barns, Great Walsingham, North Norfolk, NR22 6DR
details: Open Tues  Fr 8:00-15:00, Sat, Su 8:00-16:00. Nice selection of cakes and savory options, plus a track pump and puncture repair kits available

name: The Walled Garden Community Shop and Cafe
details: Open Mon-Sat 8:00-18:00, Sun 10:00-16:00 Beautiful walled garden cafe. Bike racks just as you enter another rack visible from the outdoor seats. Indoor seating.

name: Dafarn Newydd Village Stores & Takeaway
details: Takeaway with outdoor seating. Mon-Sat,8:00–18:30,  Sun 09:00-18:30  The most cyclist friendly shop ever,. Public toilets just over the road

name: Wellington Home and Gardens Centre
details: Open Mon-Sat 9:00-16:30, Sun 10:00-16:00. Indoor and outdoor seating.

name: Magnolia Tearooms
address: West Haddon Road, Crick,  Northampton NN6 7SQ
details: Open Thurs -Sun 9:00-16:00, Closed Mon-Wed

name: Trooper Barn
details: Open Tues-Sun 9:00-15:00. Indoor and outdoor seating. Cafe is in the barn, pub next door.

name: Black Cat Cafe
details: Open daily 11:00 - 17:30. Good cakes, brecci & lunch options

name: Kent House Coffee And Flowers
details: Open Mon - Thurs 7:30 - 17:30, Fri 7:30 – 18:30, Sat 8:00 - 18:00, Sun 9:00 - 17:00. Small amount of inside seating but tables outside in pleasant cul-de-sac area outside the station.  Great for coffee/tea/cakes - lovely to have a large glass of tap water brought out to me with the rest of my order so I am sure they would fill water bottles. There are cycle stands outside Kent House station so easy to lock the bike up

name: Moomin's
address: Unit 1 The Old Fire Station Annexe, Fairfield Rd, Market Harborough LE16 9QJ
details: Open daily 9:00 - 14:00. Owners are quite happy to have us there post cold & wet ride or warm & sweaty. Just on the edge of the main town centre, with outdoor & indoor seating. Bikes can be propped up out of sight from passing public in the rear outdoor seating area.

name: Churchinford & District Community Shop
details: Open weekdays 8:30 - 17:30, Sat 8:30 - 14:00, closed Sun. Cakes, sandwiches, snacks and cold drinks available to purchase in the shop; self-service tea and coffee; small indoor seating area. A very friendly pit-stop.

name: Shappen Cafe
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:30. Outside space for your bike. They allow dogs too (for people who cycle with their dog in a trailer). Café offers great food and drinks, seating indoors and outdoors with some covered. Friendly staff and great food, highly recommended, plus toilets available.

name: New Chapel
details: Open Sun - Thurs 10:00 - 22:00, Fri & Sat 10:00 - 23:00.

name: The Coffee Lounge
address: Unit 2A, Townfoot Industrial Estate, Brampton CA8 1SW
details: Open Wed, Fri, Sat 9:30 - 16:00, Thurs 9:30 - 18:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:00, closed Mon & Tues. Welcomes cyclists. It has a takeaway menu and there are bike racks and outside tables.

name: Stamp Coffee Shop
address: Post Office, Moor Rd, Ashover, Chesterfield S45 0AL

name: Bank Top Cafe
address: The Miners Standard, Bank Top, Winster, Matlock DE4 2DR
details: Open daily 7:00 - 12:00.

name: The Rink Bistro Kelso
details: Open daily 11:00 - 20:00. Plenty of bike parking, great coffee (Rijo) and amazing homemade cakes, plenty GF options.

name: G&T's Cafe
details: Open daily 10:00 - 16:30, closed Tues & Wed. They have a really good selection of cakes.

name: Burton Farm Cafe
address: Burton Ln, Burton Hastings, Nuneaton CV11 6RJ
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00, closed Mon. Sausage & egg sandwiches are highly recommended. Reasonably priced.

name: The Bog Myrtle Cafe
details: Open Wed - Sat 9:30 - 16:00, Sun 10:00 - 15:30, closed Mon & Tues. No food on Sundays. Great coffee, delicious cakes, breakfast/soup/sandwiches. Lovely place, with plenty of inside seating, and some picnic tables at the front too.

name: The Iron Brew

name: Badgers Hill Farm & Cidery
address: New Cut Rd, Chilham, Canterbury CT4 8BW
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00. Good variety of food and drink including hot breakfasts, cake, local produce and their own cider. Plenty of outdoor and indoor space and there are a few animals wandering around. Friendly and efficient service. Toilet facilities are basic but they have a planning application to improve those among other works.

name: The Tea Shed
address: 7, Y Wern, Pont-rhyd-y-groes, Ystrad Meurig SY25 6DF
details: Open daily 10:00 - 18:00. It's a community facility in a small village. No staff, just walk in, make yourself a drink, have a cake (if there is one) and pay in the honesty box. No toilets.

name: The Hidden Tearoom Chilham
address: Bagham Barn, Canterbury Rd, Chilham, Antiques CT4 8DU
details: Open Thurs, Fri & Sun 10:00 - 16:00, Sat 10:00 - 17:00, closed Mon - Wed. Park up in the car park (no bike rack but I chained up to a post!), go in thru the antique shop and make your way to the back where you'll find The Hidden Tearoom . The home-made cakes are ridiculously amazing, and if you pre-book you can have afternoon tea (although don't expect to do too many miles afterwards!)

name: The Hub
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30. Some indoor seating, quite a bit of outdoor but limited cover outdoors. there are toilets. Decent coffee, not massive range of food but nice cakes, paninis etc. think they have energy bars etc for cyclists too. There's an outdoor tap which you can use to fill up your bottles which is great as you don't have to keep bothering staff!

name: Holmansbridge Café
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16:00, Sat 9:00 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 - 16:00. This place is very nice & has a great menu. Near Lewes, East Sussex. In a fairly isolated farm location on Town Littleworth Road. They have a small bike rack but lots of outdoor tables to prop your ride up.

name: Childrey Stores
address: Village Stores, High St, Childrey, Wantage OX12 9UE

name: The Fika Room
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00. The cakes and coffee were good. There were lots of cyclists visiting both times I have been there. The staff were excellent, chatty and good fun.

name: The Sheds
address: The Old Post Office, Bunbury Ln, Bunbury, Tarporley CW6 9QR
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00, closed Tues. focused on hot drinks and cakes/pastries, the menu is limited but if you are looking for a mid-ride stop, this cafe provides for those needs. large indoor seated area and toilets but situated on the main throughfare there is limited bike storage areas outside. The cafe owners were certainly very welcoming to me as a cyclist.

name: Waterside Cafe
address: Oxford Sailing Club, Farmoor, Cumnor, Oxford OX2 9NS
details: Open daily 8:30 - 16:30, kitchen closes at 15:30. Great for food and lovely views across the water. You just need to push your bikes from the car park to the Cafe... 100m max!

name: Sustain Farm Shop & Cafe
address: Brinkworth Rd, Royal Wootton Bassett, Swindon SN4 8DT
details: Open daily 9:00 - 17:00. Great selection of coffee and cakes, sandwitches and refreshments( what I loved is that they use “proper” cups, plates and cutlery. No inside seating area but plenty of seats outside-covered and uncovered as well as plenty of space for bikes. Have toilets.

name: Charter Alley Village Store & Cafe
details: Open weekdays 7:30 - 18:00, Sat 8:00 - 18:00, Sun 8:00 - 15:00. Recently refurbished to provide more seating inside and improved the bike racking. Friendly and welcoming staff. Good coffee, cakes and savouries. Indoor and outdoor seating available.Toilet available.

name: Northstowe Tap and Social
address: Unit 2, The Mount, Station Rd, Northstowe, Cambridge CB24 3DS
details: Open Mon & Tues 8:30 - 22:00, Wed - Sat 8:30 - 22:00, Sun 9:00 - 22:00. Good coffee, fresh cakes, open sandwiches and pastries, good pricing and nice staff. Cycle parking available.

name: Designs Cafe
details: Open Mon-Sat 10:00-16:00. Closed Sun. Indoor  and outdoor seating. . Entrance to gardern via alley way next to nextdoor shop

name: Mill On The Fleet
address: High St, Gatehouse of Fleet, DG7 2HS
details: Open Daily 10:00-16:00  late March until end of October. Large outdoor terrace area. Take bikes into terrace, turn left at the end of the mill.

name: The Belted Galloway Visitor Centre
details: Open Tues-Sun 10:00-17:00. Indoor and outdoor seating

name: Wobbly Wheel Cafe
details: Open Mon - Sat 8:00 - 16:30, Sun 10:00 - 16:30. An excellent cafe and bike shop all together on one site. An excellent cafe and bike shop all together on one site.

name: Bythams Community Shop & Cafe
address: 46 Station Rd, Castle Bytham, Grantham NG33 4SJ

name: The Nest at Crabtree
address: Crabtree Hall Bus Centre, Little Holtby, Leeming Bar, Northallerton DL7 9LN
details: Open weekdays 9:00 - 16:00, closed weekends. A small cafe but worth a visit. On entering the park cycle all the way around the back for the cafe. You can watch the Llamascat play whilst enjoying your refreshments.

name: The Secret Garden Cafe
details: Open daily 9:30 - 17:00, Sun 10:00 - 16:00. A small cafe with a shabby chic aesthetic, among a variety of artisan stores, antique shops and the like, tucked away at the back of the town. Home cooked food and cakes. Around 20-30 seats indoors, good outdoor space including some in shelters. No bike racks but plenty of room to stand them up.Has a toilet, indoors but apparently not heated in winter.

name: The Orangery Tea Rooms
address: Whitstable Castle, Tower Hill, Whitstable CT5 2BW
details: Open daily 10:00 - 17:00. (April - September), 10:00 - 16:00 Nov - March). Offers hot and cold food and drinks: fresh scones, cakes, sausage rolls, breakfast, lunch, afternoon tea. Cosy indoor space. Outdoor tables some of which are often sheltered by gazebos and it's also possible to sit on the grass in the spacious gardens.Can be quite busy in summer when nearby Whitstable harbour is a tourist trap. There is a toilet in the cafe, others at the top of the gardens.

name: Sweet Caroline's Café
address: Corner of West Street &, Alexandra Rd, Swadlincote DE11 9DG
details: Open daily 9:30 - 16:00, closed Sun. Good idea to give notice for large groups. Plenty of space for bikes. Indoor and outdoor seating. Part of the Sharpes Museum buildings.

name: Elderslie Coffee Shop
details: Open weekdays 6:30 - 15:00, Sat 6:00 - 15:00, closed Sun. Friendly welcome and great menu. I had a black pudding and egg roll. Great  biking food! Indoor (21) and outdoor covered with awning (6) seating.  No bike parking but plenty space to put bikes. Easy to see going north, don't miss it going south.  It's part of a small shopping area with grass and picnic tables. Toilets available

name: Round Chimneys Farm
address: Round Chimneys Farm, Glanvilles Wootton, Sherborne, DT9 5QQ
details: Open daily 9:00 - 16:00, closed Mon & Tues. Plenty of space on the bike rack, amazing coffee, great cake and always a warm welcome. The owner once helped me out by giving me a spare tube when I had a flat as well!

name: Quayside Kitchen
details: Open daily 9:00 - 18:00. Behind the Rye Heritage Centre, accessed most easily from The Deals. Small cafe with outdoor space, safe parking for bikes against the fences and walls. Nice to be slightly away from the main road! Good cake and coffee, also a variety of light meals and breakfasts. Cheerful service. There is a toilet.

name: The Bee's Knees Sandwich Bar
details: Open weekdays 8:00 - 14:30, Sat 8:00 - 13:00, closed Sun. Friendly cafe set back from the A40, with a wide menu selection, good prices, great food and really fast service.

name: Greenham Control Tower & Cafe
details: Open Wed-Fri: 10:30-15:00, Sat-Sun: 10:00-16:00. Indoor and covered outdoor seating. A charity-run café in the middle of Greenham Common

name: Lochwinnoch nature reserve
details: Open daily 9:30 – 17:00. Small cafe area with indoor and uncovered outdoor picnic seating. Serves coffee and a nice range of tea,. soft drinks and sandwiches. Nice flapjacks. Bike racks.

name: The Dugout Cafébar
details: Open Fri, Sat 8:00-22:00, Sun 9:00-21:00, Tues, Wed 8:00-17:00, Closed Mon

name: Cafe Belge,
address: Nash Rd, Beachampton, Milton Keynes MK19 6FW
details: Open Fri-Sun 9:00-late. Indoor and outdoor seating. G.ood selection of hot and cold food.

name: Wild River Coffee House
details: Open Sun & Mon 12:00 - 20:00, Tues, Fri & Sat 10:00 - 16:00, closed Wed & Thurs. Run by cycle enthusiasts. Very cycle friendly, with free water refills, space for bikes to be safe, toilets and some basic spare parts and tools. Situated at the entrance to the town so very easy to access. Specialises in very good coffee and homemade food and cakes.

name: Roberto's Deli
address: Unit 1 Church Walk, St. Neots PE19 1JH
details: Open Mon, Wed-Fri  9:30 17:00, Sat 9:00-17:00,Sun 10:00-17:00. Closed Tues. Great Italian coffee, cakes savouries and pizza. Indoor seating or sit by your bikes outside. Toilets

name: Chaii Hub
details: Open Sun-Thurs 10:00-18:00, Closed Fri,Sat .Vegetarian Punjabi food and sweets. Also traditional chocolate cake, cheesecake etc. Some cycle parking by the door.

name: The Clubhouse
details: Open daily 7:00 - 16:00

name: Ground Coffee Society
address: 79 Lower Richmond Rd, Putney, London SW15 1ET

name: The Terrace Eatery
address: 7 apple Market, Kingston upon Thames, KT1 1JE

name: VIA Atelier
address: 18-19 Stable St, King's Cross, London N1C 4AB

name: Four Boroughs
address: 10 Church Rd, Crystal Palace, London SE19 2ET

name: Brickwood Coffee & Bread
details: Open Mon - Fri 7:30 - 16:00, Sat - Sun 8:00 - 17:00

name: Ernest Cafe Bar
address: 1 Boyd St, Shieldfield, Newcastle upon Tyne, NE2 1AP

name: Local NCL
address: 18 Acorn Rd, Jesmond, Newcastle upon Tyne, NE2 2DJ
details: Open daily 8:00 - 17:00

name: Pink Lane Coffee
address: 1 Pink Ln, Newcastle upon Tyne, NE1 5DW

name: Lagom Coffee Bar
address: 8 Monk St, Newcastle upon Tyne, NE1 5XD
details: Open Mon - Fri 8:30 - 16:30, Sat - Sun 10:00 - 16:30

name: Little Brew Coffee Co
details: Open Mon, Tue, Thurs, Fri 8:00 - 13:00, Sat 8:00 - 16:00, Sun 8:00 - 14:00

address: Preston Park Ave, Brighton and Hove, Brighton, BN1 6HG
details: Open Mon - Fri 10:00 - 16:30, Sat - Sun 9:00 - 18:00

details: Open Mon - Fri 9:00 - 16:00, Sat - Sun 9:00 - 17:00

address: St Ann’s Well Gardens, Somerhill Road, Hove BN3 1RP
details: Open daily 8:00 - 16:00

address: 123 Dyke Rd, Brighton and Hove, Hove BN3 1TJ
